text:
a few years ago i made the biggest change ever in my life by deciding to break free from a toxic relationship that was killing me physically, mentally, emotionally, and spiritually. since then,  i've had to adjust and survive as a single mother of three along with juggling day to day obstacles. but, i learned how to make it work and have been living a happier and healthier life since. now, i'm no stranger to overcoming challenges and leaving a toxic relationship was just one of the many struggles i've had to overcome. ***
time is running out!!!!!!
join on january 16 @ 7pm est for my free webinar (linktree in bio to sign up) where we will discuss the tools and resources i used to walk away from a toxic relationship, become a published author, and begin the journey to creating the life i always wanted. the first five people to sign up will receive a free copy of my book let mia tell it and everyone will receive my 30 day breaking toxic cycles journal for free! ***
i can't wait to grow and elevate with you and assist you with breaking the cycles that has been holding you back and keeping you from living your best life! *select the linktree in my bio to sign up!

text:
6 months ago today i was assaulted. and i'm angry. i'm angry it happened. i'm angry that i now see the world as a before and after. i had 22 years before an assault and now it's the after. i'm angry that i call it 'the thing' instead of an assault which it actually was; trivialising myself so people don't try to do it for me.

i'm angry that i blame myself. i'm a feminist and i know about the culture that exists. my dissertation surrounded the topic of rape culture and feminism. and yet, here i am, still thinking that it was me, because that's what the media and culture tell us. i'm angry it's like this. 
and maybe 6 months isn't enough time to process it? i don't want to be angry forever, and i don't think i will. i want to be hopeful; hopeful i can use this anger for something positive. i'm really fucking hopeful that our culture does start to change and that shit like this won't happen. .
.
.
.
#metoo #feminism #feminist #imfedup

text:
so this weeks piece is best viewed as tiles or grid format. it's a work in progress shot and i have great things planned for this piece which is on a brick wall. the scale is aprox 2m x 3m and the most important thing is that this is totally freehand with no grids and aiming to get a human likeness of somebody famous. so when the #metoo social media revolution hit the internet i was surprised (not really) to read that wonder woman herself  was inspired by the whole campaign. lynda carter opened up & says she was sexually abused while playing wonder woman in the iconic '70s tv show. 
carter discussed the personal experiences that have led her to become such an outspoken supporter of the #metoo movement, which spotlights women chronicling stories of sexual misconduct on social media. a longtime feminist and activist, carter was the symbol in the 1970's show for female power of her time and i remember watching the show along with the bionic woman too. i believed anything was possible for me to achieve when i was a little girl. showing the importance of these tv shows.  sadly even wonderwoman endured the industry's rampant sexual abuse and harassment.
the hypocrisy of hollywood, which has played lip service to women's empowerment for decades — all while systematically exploiting and ensuring their oppression.

carter was the symbol for female power of her time 💪🏽
on the very set of wonder woman, for instance, she said she discovered that a cameraman had drilled a hole into her dressing room. 
she said that watching the #metoo movement develop had been emotional and moving for her, and that she hoped lasting change would flow from it, “though i think it’s regional. often in red states you find racism, and where you find racism you also find sexism.” #wonderwoman #sexism #smashthepatriarchy #hollywood #lyndacarter #streetart #wonderwomanstreetart #art #instaart #spraypaint #freehand #femaleempowerment #femaleicons #hypocriticalhollywood #sexualabuse #superhero #women
name: S.o.S ARTIVIST

text:
so this weeks piece is best viewed as tiles or grid format. it's a work in progress shot and i have great things planned for this piece which is on a brick wall. the scale is aprox 2m x 3m and the most important thing is that this is totally freehand with no grids and aiming to get a human likeness of somebody famous. so when the #metoo social media revolution hit the internet i was surprised (not really) to read that wonder woman herself  was inspired by the whole campaign. lynda carter opened up & says she was sexually abused while playing wonder woman in the iconic '70s tv show. 
carter discussed the personal experiences that have led her to become such an outspoken supporter of the #metoo movement, which spotlights women chronicling stories of sexual misconduct on social media. a longtime feminist and activist, carter was the symbol in the 1970's show for female power of her time and i remember watching the show along with the bionic woman too. i believed anything was possible for me to achieve when i was a little girl. showing the importance of these tv shows.  sadly even wonderwoman endured the industry's rampant sexual abuse and harassment.
the hypocrisy of hollywood, which has played lip service to women's empowerment for decades — all while systematically exploiting and ensuring their oppression.

carter was the symbol for female power of her time 💪🏽
on the very set of wonder woman, for instance, she said she discovered that a cameraman had drilled a hole into her dressing room. 
she said that watching the #metoo movement develop had been emotional and moving for her, and that she hoped lasting change would flow from it, “though i think it’s regional. often in red states you find racism, and where you find racism you also find sexism.” #wonderwoman #sexism #smashthepatriarchy #hollywood #lyndacarter #streetart #wonderwomanstreetart #art #instaart #spraypaint #freehand #femaleempowerment #femaleicons #hypocriticalhollywood #sexualabuse #superhero #women
name: S.o.S ARTIVIST

text:
so this weeks piece is best viewed as tiles or grid format. it's a work in progress shot and i have great things planned for this piece which is on a brick wall. the scale is aprox 2m x 3m and the most important thing is that this is totally freehand with no grids and aiming to get a human likeness of somebody famous. so when the #metoo social media revolution hit the internet i was surprised (not really) to read that wonder woman herself  was inspired by the whole campaign. lynda carter opened up & says she was sexually abused while playing wonder woman in the iconic '70s tv show. 
carter discussed the personal experiences that have led her to become such an outspoken supporter of the #metoo movement, which spotlights women chronicling stories of sexual misconduct on social media. a longtime feminist and activist, carter was the symbol in the 1970's show for female power of her time and i remember watching the show along with the bionic woman too. i believed anything was possible for me to achieve when i was a little girl. showing the importance of these tv shows.  sadly even wonderwoman endured the industry's rampant sexual abuse and harassment.
the hypocrisy of hollywood, which has played lip service to women's empowerment for decades — all while systematically exploiting and ensuring their oppression.

carter was the symbol for female power of her time 💪🏽
on the very set of wonder woman, for instance, she said she discovered that a cameraman had drilled a hole into her dressing room. 
she said that watching the #metoo movement develop had been emotional and moving for her, and that she hoped lasting change would flow from it, “though i think it’s regional. often in red states you find racism, and where you find racism you also find sexism.” #wonderwoman #sexism #smashthepatriarchy #hollywood #lyndacarter #streetart #wonderwomanstreetart #art #instaart #spraypaint #freehand #femaleempowerment #femaleicons #hypocriticalhollywood #sexualabuse #superhero #women

text:
to explain narcissistic abuse to anyone, is extremely challenging. it’s difficult for anyone to wrap their head around — ourselves included. the other night i told one of my gfs about the sexual abuse and exploitation — her jaw dropped to the floor and was rendered speechless. she just couldn’t fathom any of it and she loathed narky narc to begin with. she always found him slimy and arrogant.
-
this friend was compassionate toward me and after letting it sink in, she was apologetic that this had happened to me. not everyone is as understanding. most aren’t, truth be told. it’s almost impossible for people to process, particularly if they’re friends with both of you.
-
don’t try to make people understand. you may want to scream it from the rooftops of how much of a sneaky slimy bastard he is, but pay attention — not everyone has your best interests at heart. your healing and forward movement #narcfree is important, so choose wisely when it comes to confiding in people. there are flying monkeys out there.
-
stay focused on yourself and don’t give any emotion to memories or ideas about them. it’s energetic supply that you require to heal — don’t give it to them. you’ve got this. 🖤
-
thank you @escaping_from_the_narcissist for the meme.
-

text: camel pose can be compressive, especially how most teachers guide you into it with a “drop-back” approach. to me you would learn to drop back into full wheel pose first, you learn to go from the ground up. i use the same approach when teaching camel. what’s interesting here is the purpose of showing the assist is to help everyone find a way to lift and lengthen, for less compression. through kinesthetic learning (touch) many people find more clarity in the actions. that being said, when i posted this on igtv i got many responses saying this was completely inappropriate and crossing the line etc. for me personally i know that there is no sexual intent or desire to cause physical harm toward my good friend @theyogarina while my wife @dancinbecka holds the phone. in addition beau voluntarily demonstrated. as a society i appreciate that we are trying to wake up and be more transparent. i worry that we confuse actions and intentions. i wonder if i were female or if beau was male if i would have received the same feedback? what do you think? does this cross the line for you, should we leave touch to handshakes and high fives unless it’s with a significant other? where is the line for you?

text:
in whistle blowers association we have started a project that could change many lives. and we only ask for 30 seconds of your knowledge.
we have decided to speak up about an issue that may have affected you, me, your friend, your sister and half of the women in the world. workplace harassment.
information is the most powerful tool we have. this is why we ask you to share your story, your knowledge or anything you want related to workplace harassment with us. what may seem insignificant to you could be life-changing for someone else. we help you, you help others. together we can make a difference. please send your ideas, articles and questions to:
michaelantonrouse@gmail.com

don’t forget to follow us to stay updated on all information and stories!

text:
i’m trusting god to send 29 of the right people for this unmute yourself anthology campaign. people who know the value of what is about to unfold. people who are ready to take advantage of this opportunity to make income and an even larger impact. .
.

if you’re feeling his tap on your shoulder, say yes and get ready for an amazing ride. .
.we’re not half-stepping. this campaign will be done in excellence.

the investment (depending on the level) covers:

graphic design
editing
marketing
pr
publishing costs
printing costs 
website work
email campaign
event planner 
event space 
branded t-shirts
other branded merchandise
photography
videography
project management 
social media campaign

this isn’t your average anthology project.

contributors are respected as more than vehicles for money. so they will receive: .
.
•storytelling training from me (to make sure the book is cohesive)
•book real estate of 2000-2500 words
•adjusted net revenue share .
•10 physical copies of the books (which they may sell to recoup some of their investment)
•recorded virtual summit interview and live virtual summit discussion, which gives access to multiple platforms
•social media exposure
•2 unmute yourself unference (conference) tickets which they may sell to recoup some of their investment .
.*stage speaking opportunity
*media exposure
*back room selling at unference .
.
as you can see, this unmute yourself campaign is not a game. .
.
this is divinely ordained and i’m trusting god to send the right people. .
.
if you’re feeling the tap, apply (#linkinbio 2nd button). *only for the vip contributor package.
.
.
.

“where’s wray?“ fucking triggered. .

watching the docuseries by the incredible #dreamhampton had me feeling a lot, seeing a lot and still has me sifting through - a lot.
.

dear abusers, we’re fucking done.

text_retweet:
a lot of people i meet are uncomfortable with how i talk about racism and sexism.
.
i’m 💯 ok with that.
.
as a white cis-gendered able-bodied man, i’m at the top of the privilege chain.
.
my goal over the next 40 years is to use that huge privilege to help tear down the generational institutionalized systems of racism and sexism we have in america.
.
i get it if that makes you feel uncomfortable.
.
i just don’t care. 
i’m going to keep going.
.
if you’re one of the believers like me, say so in the comments! let’s do this together.
. . . . . .
.
.
.
.

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
here are some options for at-home protein treatments for hair:

egg mask.

you can make a protein treatment for natural hair with eggs you have at home. eggs are probably the best protein treatment for heat damaged natural hair because they are rich not only in protein, but in beneficial enzymes. egg is a good natural protein treatment for damaged hair because hair that has been treated via heat or product tends to be very brittle and very dry. for a protein treatment for natural fine hair, use the entire egg. beat until frothy and apply evenly to hair and scalp, cover with a cap or warm towel, and let mixture sit for 20 minutes. for a natural protein treatment for frizzy hair or oily hair, use only the egg whites. this egg protein treatment for natural hair can be used as an at-home protein treatment for hair every two weeks or on a monthly basis.

yogurt.
yogurt, sour cream and similar dairy products contain not only protein, but lactic acid, which cleanses your hair while the fat in the dairy moisturizes it. this is a great weekly treatment that will revitalize and bring luster back to your hair. to create an extra powerful homemade protein conditioner, add an egg into your yogurt mixture. let your mixture sit for up to 20 minutes before washing out.

avocado.
for powerful results, try a protein treatment for natural hair with avocado. avocados are not only loaded with protein and nutrients, but their high-fat content has great benefits when applied to hair. avocados repair hair damage, strengthen hair strands, and make hair less dry, brittle and prone to breakage. mix half of a smashed up avocado with 2 tablespoons of mayonnaise (which contains egg protein) and apply this homemade protein conditioner to your hair weekly.

coconut oil.
coconut oil or coconut butter is rich in healthy fats and proteins that are great as a natural protein treatment for damaged hair. applying a mask of coconut oil to your hair can provide a very economical, deep-moisturizing treatment that can give you great results.

text:
yesterday, i went to my first gymnastics meet as a coach! 😭 growing up, i was a competitive gymnast. both in childhood and later in life, this sport has made tremendous impact on my life. it has taught me how to be fierce, brave, strong, independent, confident, and it gave me an insatiable work ethic!
. 
gymnastics is not just a sport of the body. more than anything, gymnastics is a sport of the mind. it will bring you face to face with things that scare you the shit out of you and it will reward you for facing them by showing you that you are capable of literally anything that you allow your energy to flow into.
. 
moving my body has always been necessary to reach beyond the mental and emotional blocks standing in my way. not only is it a relief to step away from the energy of blocks, but it is truly miraculous and healing to transmute those blocks.
. 
i see everything in my life as divine. it's no accident i grew up a gymnast. it's no accident that i take great honor and respect for my role as a gymnastics coach now. it's no accident that this sport has moulded me as a person and that it continues to do so.
. 
i was born for this.
. 
the world of gymnastics is admist an incredible transformation. the collective athletic soul of this nation is healing. 🙏 if you were, or currently are a gymnast who has experienced a trauma in your sport such as injury, emotional or sexual abuse, or mental blocks keeping you from your higher level skills, then i would love for you to reach out to me. we just might be soul mates! 💕 i am here to help you uncover your emotional traumas, and be a supportive guide in your healing.
. 
your story has been no accident either. you were born to change the world and i truly believe you will. i love you! 💓
.

please follow the link in my bio to reach out to me. 😘

text: for this episode, we wanted to help support survivors whose stories are, unfortunately, far too commonplace to be featured on our show. to that end, we are featuring @safe_alliance as our cause of the week. check out their page to get an idea of the important work they do! according to research presented by safealliance.org, 1-in-3 women will be impacted by sexual assault or domestic violence during their life time. three women are killed each day in the usa by an intimate partner. every 2 minutes someone in the usa is sexually assaulted. one in every 4 girls, and 1 in every 6 boys will be sexually assaulted before their 18th birthday. if you are as horrified by these statistics as we are, please join us in supporting the cause. you can donate directly on their site safealliance.org, or you can support us on patreon, where 100% of donations beyond our minimal operating costs will be funneled to a new causes like this one each week. https://www.patreon.com/stftalk. thank you!

text: see what people are saying about candy apple butterscotch, #newauthor rebecca macceile’s debut publication. “this is an impactful read if you have ever experienced any sort of abuse. i appreciate the author’s candor and willingness to write with such openness. she takes responsibility for herself as much as she describes the lasting effects of trauma.” “it is worth the read. it’s about a woman empowered and, my god, that is a wonderful thing indeed.” “the author gets to the point while still painting a very clear and definite picture for the readers and i love that. the accounts of the trauma are laid out in such a way that you know what’s happening and are able to imagine it but you aren’t bombarded with intense graphic imagery, which i appreciate as a survivor myself. would definitely recommend!” “this amazingly written gem takes you inside the author's world and keeps you there, making you feel like a discreet "bug on the wall." i could not put it down.” “i wish everyone would write a memoir. it would be so much easier to understand people. i haven’t been through anything as violent or traumatic, but i think this story is relatable in a lot of ways. it just makes me see a lot of things differently in every day life. it’s a big eye opener.” #onsalenow at the #linkinbio. #kindle and #paperback versions available! also for members of #amazonprime, candy apple butterscotch is available in the #kindlelendinglibrary as well as through #kindleunlimitedbooks! that’s right you can read for #free. #nonfictionbooks #memoir #metoo #ptsdsurvivor #kindlestoryteller2018  #kindledirectpublishing #onsalenow #paperback #kindlelendinglibrary #bookrecommendations #indieauthor #authorsofinstagram #amazon #readforfreekll

text:
there are things on my “to-do” list that have been lingering for some time.  i’m not proud of that.  i’ve circled around the reasoning for why we don’t do what we need to do.  it could be something that will get us closer to achieving our goals or something that is mundane and just needs to be completed.  what is the underlying factor that’s holding us back?  is it fear or is there something more? .🤔
.
.
i have this task that is rather big that i need to finish.  it won’t take me long.  maybe a few hours, but i resist it so much.  every day i think about this task and it haunts me. 🤦🏼‍♀️
.
.
what i’ve realized is that the pain of not completing the task is more painful than the pain of actually doing the work.  the amount of time and energy spent thinking about what needs to be done is far worse than the few hours it would take to start, finish, and put that task behind you. 🙌🏼💯
.
.
steven pressfield describes resistance in his book the war of art.  there will always be resistance in life.  resistance may be pushing you back, but it is not stopping you from achieving.  push through resistance and meet freedom on the other side.  #mondaymotivation ❤️🤗❤️

text:
女人迷專訪日本 #metoo 代表—伊藤詩織 原音重現
⠀
#關於伊藤詩織
⠀
2017 年 12 月 29 日，日本正舉國歡慶新年，熱鬧跨年的前夕，紐約時報刊登了一張巨幅照片：一個日本女孩站在黑暗中，撐著纖弱的透明傘抵擋冷雨，標題這樣寫：she broke japan's silence on rape （她打破日本對性侵的沉默）。格外鬧騰的時節，這則報導安靜得震耳欲聾，畫面中表情沉靜的女人，就是伊藤詩織。
⠀
為什麼紐約時報決定以大篇幅報導這位年輕日本女性？故事必須回到報導刊出的七個月以前（2017 年 5 月），日本記者伊藤詩織具名露臉、現身指控前 tbs 華盛頓分社領導人山口敬之對她性侵。山口敬之不只是資深記者，還是安倍首相御用的傳記作者，他曾貼身與安倍共同進出，陪打高爾夫、參與各式活動，在日本新聞界極具影響力。
⠀
事實上，這起性侵事件發生得更早：2015 年，那一年，伊藤即對山口提出刑事指控，不過日本當時幾無討論與報導。2016 年，檢察官判定證據不足不起訴。山口敬之非但沒受任何懲處，還繼續在原職位大發議論、寫專欄、上節目。
⠀
直到 2017 年，伊藤決定現身、露面指控，《紐約時報》東京分社長 motoko rich 決定針對此案展開長達六個月的調查。約莫在同一時間，歐美捲起 #metoo 運動，這則報導釋出後，使伊藤成為日本 #metoo 代表人物，她的遭遇先是震撼國際社會，才以「家醜外揚」之姿回到日本，獲得國內正視。
——————
面對性侵害，說出真相是唯一的選擇。
⠀
2018 年，台灣也發生導演性侵案件，當時女星柯奐如在臉書上說到：「唯有好好凝視，才有機會找到出口。選擇逃避，並不會心安，選擇沉默，心裡的傷痛，無法自行消失。」
⠀
關於性暴力，說出口很困難，但是我們願意陪你一起走過。
——————
想了解伊藤詩織的故事，女人迷搜尋「#伊藤詩織」
#女人迷 #womany #metoo #metoomovement #genderimpactaward

text:
| emotional self leading |
businessprostitution

diese wort kam mir als erstes in den sinn, als ich eindringlich gebeten wurde mit einem wichtigen mietinteressenten privat zeit zu verbringen, um einen abschluss voran zu bringen. 
ich tat es nicht. ich bin frau, nicht nur körper! meine zeit ist wertvoll und ich entscheide, wem ich sie schenke! ich entscheide, wer mir nah kommen darf, wer in meinen tanzbereich tritt. ich entscheide, wie wichtig karriere gegenüber selbstwert ist! und der abschluss hätte ein übergehen meiner werte in keinster weise gerechtfertig. 
die bitte meines chefs damals war für mich krönung und die letzte bitte, die er an mich richtete.
leider ist es alltag, dass frauen dazu aufgefordert werden, oder es aus dem willen nach mehr anerkennung, mehr erfolg, mehr was auch immer... tun oder tun sollen. wie thekenware... ich rede bewusst nicht von denen, die es geil finden,... ich kenne einige frauen, die im laufe der zeit sich selbst nicht mehr liebenswert, nicht gut genug, teilweise als wertlos oder sogar widerlich... empfanden. die sich schämten und ihren platz in ihrer welt verloren. und das betrifft nicht nur angestellte. das ist so unglaublich traurig und beschämend für die gesellschaft.

leider ist es alltag, dass frauen dazu aufgeforde werden, oder es aus dem willen nach mehr anerkennung, mehr erfolg, mehr was auch immer... tun oder tun sollen. wie thekenware... ich rede bewusst nicht von denen, die es geil finden,... ich kenne einige frauen, die im laufe der zeit sich selbst nicht mehr liebenswe, nicht gut genug, teilweise als welos oder sogar widerlich... empfanden. die sich schämten und ihren platz in ihrer welt verloren. und das betrifft nicht nur angestellte. das ist so unglaublich traurig und beschämend für die gesellschaft.

du entscheidest!!!

text:
good morning and happy monday!  today’s challenge ~ name one thing you like about yourself ... now name one more!
.
how did you do with that?  was it easy to identify 2 things you like about yourself?  or did it take you a bit of time?  being able to identify our positives, our strengths and to like ourselves is part of improving our self-worth. .
if you want to take this challenge to the next level, make a list of 50 things you like about yourself.  50, you ask?! yep, 50.  now, the “rules” to this challenge is to do it yourself — don’t ask those around you what they like about you and don’t use a thesaurus.  the goal is to improve your self-worth. if you ask others, and you get upset with that person you will discount what they say.  if we do this ourselves, it will mean more. 💜

text:
父の知り合いの方にお誘いいただいて、
オリックス劇場にて
something rotten!観てきた。

2015年にbroadwayでtony賞も助演男優賞で受賞しているらしい。

観劇していて思い出した。
2000年頃の中学２年の頃、
誰も喋ってくれないから
ひたすら学校で作詞していたのも
いつのまにかいくつか机から無くなったりしてたなぁと。

ちなみに私と同姓同名のアダルト女優もいたらしい。
同級生というか当時の女の幼なじみに布山友紀子って女の子がいてよく胸が大きいから
『将来、アダルト女優になりそう』って
言われてた。
ちなみにそのお父さんは広告会社に勤めていて、
私と同じ名前のそういう人が本当に当時いたらしいことを後々誰かに教えて貰った。
実は既にこの前の小学校から始まってた訳で。

text:
i invited people from my father's acquaintance,
at the orix theater
i have seen something rotten.

it seems that in 2015 the tony award at the broadway was also awarded with a supporting actor award.
i remembered it at the theater.
as i was in my second year of junior high school around 2000, 
because nobody speaks,
 i was losing something from my desk at the school just before i was writing lyrics.
by the way it seems that there was also an adult actress with the same name as me.
as a classmate, there is a girl who is yukiko fuyama with her childhood friend at that time, well
"in the future, it seems to be an adult actress"
i was told.
by the way the father worked for an advertising company and someone later taught me that such a person with the same name as me was truly back then.
actually, i started from an elementary school before this.

text:
through back 2013. 16y/o
i was really sad a long time because i gained double of my weight because of my psychopharmacine from this to now but i accept it now and in some kind i really like the way i am now. because even though i had a quiet perfect body i was one of the sadest girls... i was hated and bullied by many people and i was crazy for that one boy who didn't love me and i couldn't handle it because i had no control over my hidden autistic self noone knew about . and it's somehow weird because many that see this picture may think that i was a really happy girl because of this one fake smile. since my depression, autism and some other issues i don't want to talk about got diagnosed as i was 19 my life begun to brighten up. and the funny thing is that now i don't know what was going on and who's fault it is only that i had a big problem and i had to deal with it alone. .
.

.
.
.
.

text:
pms stands for premenstrual syndrome – it's the combination of symptoms that some women suffer from a week or so before their period. symptoms appear before your period starts (as many as five days) and will disappear during your period. pms is a group of changes that can affect you on many levels and varies person to person. they can be physical, emotional, or behavioral.

physical signs
-weight gain
-cramps
-swollen hands and feet
-bloated tummy
-tender breast
-pimples
-hunger
-constipation or diarrhea

emotional signs
-mood swings
-tense or anxious
-angry outbursts
-don't want to be with people
-feel overwhelmed or out of control
-can't sleep
-crying

behavioral signs
-forget things
-loss of mental focus
-tired
.
.

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

the accounts were suspended because facebook received repos that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided ceifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received repos that, contrary to the ceifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending fuher information.

special counsel robe mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal repoed in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
(1/3) "in the fruit of our womb, christina is given a chance at a new life with a wealthy manhattan couple who decide to adopt her. their intentions seem beyond reproach. but what starts off as a perfect utopian family, quickly turns into a nightmare.
while doing research for the film, i came across some staggering statistics. it became clear that child sex abuse (especially in foster families) is much more common than we allow ourselves to believe. 
obviously, not all of these people are clinical diagnosed as mentally ill, the majority are ordinary citizens that live according to societal rules. if they are extreme in anything, it’s their conformity. and yet they cross over to the territory of “the unthinkable” with such ease. they must find a way to normalize it somehow – at least to themselves."
stay tuned this week and next as we share more comments from director marina shron about the process of researching & writing #thefruitofourwomb
#tfoow #ourwomb

it’s about living within.

it’s about finding all the things you love about yourself, and making those things more pronounced.

it’s about discovering things you want to change but finding the courage to love yourself as you are right now.

learning to live and love my whole me...what a journey to be on. 😘✌🏻

text:
what is the sexual harassment case against rajkumar hirani ? 
in an email dated november 3, 2018, a woman accused director rajkumar hirani of sexual harassment. the email was addressed to hirani's frequent collaborator vidhu vinod chopra, his wife anupama chopra, scriptwriter abhijat joshi and shelly chopra dhar, who is the director of 'ek ladki ko dekha toh aisa laga' and also vinod chopra's sister. 
the complainant was working as hirani's assistant for the film 'sanju', during which the alleged incident took place. according to the email, the complainant was harassed from march to september 2018. 
#metoo #asiaville

text:
me too movement...
.
.
the #metoo movement is a movement against sexual harassment and sexual assault. .
.  origin 
the phrase #metoo was coined by tarana burke in 2006 as part of a campaign to promote "empowerment through empathy" among women of color who have experienced sexual abuse, particularly within underprivileged communities.
.
.  popular...
fast forward to 2017, #metoo became viral on social media in an attempt to demonstrate the widespread prevalence of sexual assault and harassment, especially in the workplace. it followed soon after the sexual abuse allegations against a high profile celebrity. .
.  properly defined...
creator tarana burke is quite specific about the  goals for the #metoo movement which includes..
1# processing all untested rape kits in the united states,

2# investigating the vetting of teachers.

3# better protecting children at school.

4# updating sexual harassment policies, and improving training in workplaces, places of worship, and schools. .
.
everyone in a community, including men and women, must take action in order to make the #metoo movement a success. .
.

text:
tw//:vegan/food (tw is for anyone who has a ed or doesn't want to hear about me being vegan fyi)
.
.
i made the decision about a week ago to go vegan. i decided this for myself, and i would never try to guilt my partners, or others to go vegan. -
i made this decision because i am autistic (autism spectrum disorder), and sensory issues go with that, especially around food. i relied on meat, dairy, any other animal products to give me all my nutrients. when they couldn't possibly give me those. - 
i don't want people to think that going vegan solves sensory issues. i don't want you guys to think i am saying that. it has been very hard. yet 100% worth it. it causes me to get up, prepare my food, write down what i like, what i don't like. do research around what to substitute! know what i need to eat to get the right amount of protein, and other nutrients. -
for me going vegan was 100% worth it. it was also a big factor of knowing what was going into my body, and has helped me recover from sexual abuse. again, going vegan isn't for everyone, but i have noticed that my body functions better, my tummy is happier, my brain is operating faster, my mental health has improved (some), and feelings around/about food has improved!
food:
1 cup of almond milk 
1 apple cinnamon rice cake 
1 sliced banana 
1/4 cup of peanutbutter

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
this 10 year throwback challenge has really weighed heavy on my heart and my mind. and my reasoning for posting this is that maybe there are some women out there going through the same thing.
alot of people didnt know that 10 years ago i was in an incredibly abusive relationship. not only physical, spiritual, emotional... it nearly killed me. i could write a book on my year experience with him!
glow up is one thing..and lordt i know my glow up is real 😂
the photo on the left were photos i had to ask my mum to take of me. can you imagine asking your mum to take photos of your bruises?? i can only thank god i made it out alive and for all the blessings i have received. 
i am stronger than ever. i have 2 beautiful children. a wonderful husband.
he is still out there. and im still standing. 
if you are going through the same thing please feel free to message me. you are stronger than you know. god has your back. #survivor #abusesurvivor #metoo #strongwomen

text:
//#metoo i skolan// #tystiklassen för över ett år sen visade att skolan långt ifrån är en trygg plats för alla. vad har hänt på din skola sedan dess?

i höstas föreläste malin averstad ryd och johan petterson i metoder och verktyg för en skola fri från sexuella trakasserier för 1 314 elever och personal från 208 högstadium och gymnasium i hela sverige. heldagskonceptet togs fram av make equal i samarbete med backainitivet, som är ett initiativ från sveriges elevkårer, sveriges elevråd, sveriges elevråd – svea, lärarförbundet skolledare och sveriges skolledarförbund (mer info på backa.org). vi är stolta över att ha varit en del av viktiga samtal och förändringsarbete!

nu är vårterminen igång och arbetet med en skola fri från sexuella trakasserier fortsätter. vill du att vi kommer till er skola? säg hej på kim@makeequal.se

syntolkning: ett bildspel med foton från turnen, där malin och johan föreläser för olika grupper. först syns en skärmdump av en artikel i svenska dagbladet med rubriken “skolor vill ta krafttag mot kränkningar” samt ett foto från en av föreläsningarna med johan.

text:
hello 😊
je tenais à témoigner d’une chose incroyable qui m’est arrivé avec ce merveilleux style de vie 🤩🤩🤩🤩 hormis la merveilleuse transformation physique j’ai vécu 🙏🏻 je souffrais de ce qu’on appelle la rosacée, pour celles qui ne connaissent pas c est qu’on a des plaques rouges, chaudes, qui tirent, et s’étalent sur les joues, le cou et le nez 👃 
lorsqu’il fait froid ça empire, lorsqu’il fait chaud c’est terrible car on rougît encore plus, idem si on mange épicé 🌶 on boit un verre de vin, si on est stressé ou timide etc..... bref on est très souvent écarlate 😭
ça me complexait beaucoup et j’ai essayé des tonnes de crèmes miraculeuses qui coûtent très cher mais rien a faire 😭😭😭
j’ai vu des dermatologues, médecins, spécialistes en tout genre etc mais 
rien à faire 😓😭😫 depuis que je suis ce style de vie et consomment mes 30 fruits, légumes et baies par jour mon inflammation à beaucoup diminué et je s’ouvre beaucoup moins 🙏🏻🙏🏻 je me sens moins mal à l’aise et n’aie plus peur d’être en publique rouge comme une tomate 🍅 
donc c’est devenu mon astuce beauté au naturel et ça m’a fait économiser beaucoup de sous et d’énergie 🙏🏻🤩🙏🏻🤩🙏🏻 #demplan

text:
kali
it was my mother’s fault that she birthed
me on the banks of kaveri
for try as they did they could not wash the black alluvial soil off my skin

kali
this one just got baked a little longer in the oven laughs my father when
my mother guiltily presents him with yet another daughter
one whose skin only a paddy farmer could love.

kali
i am six when i am made to understand that
i who was proudly showing off my 99% in maths was less than my classmate,
at least i’m fairer than you she says,
sadly looking down at her own 73% marks

kali
the shame i feel looking at my white face black neck makeup at my arangetram
the shame
is for the secret pleasure that even though i look like a clown, i am fair
for two hours

kali
i burn my skin to a crisp with hydrogen peroxide, congratulations.
i now possess blonde sideburns to contrast my black skin.

kali
the proud mother of a prospective groom, who insisted on a fair skinned bride
for her son who was ‘white as milk’
amma told her off in no uncertain terms that her daughter
is dark as decoction and only when you mix the two.
do you get rich aromatic
coffee

kali
the boy who said your skin shines
like burnished copper.
i let him go, i thought he was lying.
boris becker declared that the only time
he noticed that his girlfriend was black
was when he saw how beautiful her skin
looked against his white sheets

kali
touching my husband’s peachy creamy skin when we make love
wondering how he could find me desirable

kali
lakme has three shades white, off-white and peach
the joy i feel when i purchase my first compact
at heera panna smugglers market
at age 26
it is the mythical, never seen before mac compact,
in the pre- manmohan singh era
and it is the exact shade of my skin,
nc45
they got me. they knew i existed.
i had a number.
(continues in the first comment) 
by- hema gopinath sah
________________________

text:
metoo® je registračná ochranná známka spoločnosti 
shenzhen huisen toys co. 💗
firma bola založená v roku 2004 v čínskom meste šen-čen. ⛩

text:
life is dangerous. some of our most harrowing experiences have happened outside of the bush. let me tell you about this one. i was sure we were going to die...for about 10 seconds. spoiler: we didn’t.  it was just before christmas. misty and i had driven to anchorage. the best shopping happens in anchorage. we had some capital in our possession. naturally, we needed to spend it. it was a good night. we stacked deep in business supplies and picked up a few more gifts for the overly spoiled childs. i even picked up two sport coats. you can’t be a professional without looking good. that’s why i’m still an amateur.
we finished up our shopping and headed home. our little toyota corolla was packed floor to ceiling. my hat and face mask were stuffed in the far back corner of the rear windshield. more on that later. i had a new laptop, a new camcorder, some new software, a ton of leather, and my two fancy sport coats all in the backseat. we’d had a good night. 
we were driving along, discussing our lives and our future. we were making plans and talking about strategies. we talked about the kids. “i think i’m going to introduce ella to star wars.” i knew she would love it. something we could bond over. i had made a promise to god almighty at her birth (another story). star wars wasn’t in it. i’ll explain that later. i don’t care much who understands it.
we’re driving along. i mentioned the book “how to win friends and influence people”. i never did read that book. the road was clear of snow, but had an icy sheen on it. it was cold that night. the road was black. the night was dark. there was no other traffic.
“moose!” misty shouted frantically. there was no moose on the road, and then there was. it was standing broadside. it’s hide was a perfect match for the black road and the black night. no eye shine. it just appeared in front of us. too late to do anything. it was standing directly in our lane. my first reaction was a no no. i slammed on the breaks. my second reaction was a no no. i cut my wheel to the left. at that point i remembered my first mistake and pumped the break so as not to spin us out of control. didn’t matter. cont in comments ⬇️

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

.
.

text:
astrologie en millenials (de babys van 1980-2000) gaan bijna hand in hand samen. en voornamelijk hoog opgeleide, jonge vrouwen lijken massaal astrologie en de maan te omarmen. 
maar waar komt de interesse vandaan? al jaren werden we plat gebombardeerd met de horoscoopstukjes van 3 regels in elk meisjes-/vrouwenblad en krant, maar de laatste twee jaar heeft het weer echt een opmars gemaakt onder alle baarmoederdragende personen. is het vanwege de economische ellende waar wij de afgelopen jaren in hebben geleefd? werpen we met #metoo en #femisist het patriarchaat dan eindelijk om ver? 
wat denk jij? versterken we ons vrouwelijkheid met astrologie of is het ook een manier om om te gaan met onzekerheden die op ons pad kunnen komen?

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

🇬🇧 hi,
thanks so so much to candice @chroniqueuse6 for reading and reviewing our street harassment anthology 🙏
she liked the fact each story denounces a different aspect of harassment or harassers. there are, sadly, many ways to be a victim and that’s why sometimes you can think you’re not or you don’t deserve to be considered like this. but the truth is no one should intervene in your life, especially without your consent!
have a great time ⛅️

text:
gorgeous diamirza and rajkumar hirani 
actor diamirza who played maanyata dutt's role in sanju movie, responded and said that while she is deeply distressed by the news, she feels an official inquiry must be conducted. she said, "i am deeply distressed by this news. as someone who has known and respect raju sir for 15 years, i can only hope that a due official enquiry is conducted. he is one of the most decent human beings i have ever worked with and i think it would be grossly unjust on my part to speak on this as i do not know the details." دیا میرزا که نقش همسر سانجی دات را ،در فیلم  سانجو بازی کرده در واکنش به ازار جنسی کارگردان مشهور بالیوود راج کومار هیرانی ، پاسخ داد و گفت : "من از این موضوع عمیقا ناراحت هستم. من به  عنوان کسی که پانزده سال هست که راج را می شناسم و به او احترام می گذارم، تنها می توانم امیدوار باشم که یک تحقیق  رسمی مطرح شود. او یکی از شایسته ترین انسان هایی است که تاکنون با او کار کرده ام و من فکر می کنم خیلی ناعادلانه است که به صحبت در مورد این موضوع بپردازم چون من جزئیات را نمی دانم. "
@diamirzaofficial

text:
women are changing. i've been noticing it for a while. with a passionate side hustle, a strong independent decision, a push through the glass ceiling....little signs that pop up to show me ➡️women everywhere are changing. 💕we are becoming more alive, embracing our freedom that has been so deeply fought for by those before us.💕 we've seen in the #metoo movement, in #heforshe , in the #gendergap fight. 😇 women are stepping into their place. ➡️ and for the first time in my life, this summer, i have seen it all around me as i take adventures with my kids. the women at the pool are confidently wearing their bathers, not covering themselves out of insecurity 👙 the mothers are walking their prams in the evenings, wearing their tiny shorts & fitted tanks. 🏃‍♀️ the 60 year old life-long friends having coffee together, are wearing mini skirts & body cons ☕ women are loving themselves more, loving their bodies more. we are saying #effyourbeautystandards and actually meaning it. 💕 the message of self love and confidence is getting through. it's changing us.  after a lifetime of feeling the pain of women hating themselves, of fighting that myself, of watching my mother cover herself and my friends mock their 'mum bodies', there is finally a light 🌟 i, for one, am so bloody glad to see it. not just for the freedom it brings the rest of my life, but because the future i want for my daughter is now becoming possible. 😍 she can feel confident in her body, every day. she can feel freedom in what she wears, every day. she can be courageous in pursuing what sets her soul on fire, every day. she can stand on the shoulders of women who have fought to create this life, and feel the exhilaration of a life wide open, with anything possible, every day. 💕 all because we started believing we could wear tiny clothes without shame. so go for the bikinis, ladies. go for the tiny skirts, the low cut tee, the fitted jeans..go for what makes you feel confident and sexy af, because you're not just doing it for you..you're doing it for our daughters. 
#day14 #60dayconfidencechallenge #doitforher #confidentbody #summerbody #allbodiesaresummerbodies

text:
i’ve had a troubling week inside my noggin. many intrusive thoughts, lots of mini-flashbacks, lots of thoughts of the assault and any and all events linked to it from getting overly drunk with my ex and ex flatmate to crying on my own in woodford and receiving a vicious note from one of my flatmates essentially telling me to stfu or else, missing london yet not feeling a great sense of warmth for wanting to ever go back, anxiety, depression and massive sleeping problems from insomnia to oversleeping. i even caught myself scratching at my arms which i haven’t done in a couple of months now. 
i’m about to get my clean on and am at peace that if i need to get obsessive with it, it’s more than allowed and is one of my coping mechanisms as long as i see it that way.
i’m very self aware and aware that i am not screwing things up but feel like i am, constantly.
i saw a great post earlier this morning that, in a nutshell, read:
stop making people with mental health problems feel bad for their symptoms...we overthink, overcompensate, are sorry and are trying. 
i’m trying. i’m just not sure if it’s enough for anyone else but me and my little man.

text:
esta imagen que he sacado de las stories de @feminancy1 me encanta porque me parece que refleja a la perfección la palabra sororidad.

me imagino a mujeres de diferentes edades, con distintas religiones o sin tener ninguna, de cualquier país del mundo, que entre sus piernas tienen un sexo que no define lo que son. seguramente con una educación distinta, serán de diferentes clases sociales e incluso puede que tengan una ideología que no se parezca en nada a la de su compañera.

lo que sí sé es que están abrazadas por una causa común: el feminismo. y por eso en mi imaginación recreo la imagen de que se han podido apoyar unas a otras diciéndose que “si tocan a una, nos tocan a todas”. con total seguridad cada una tiene una historia, más o menos lejana de la violencia machista que ejerce el patriarcado contra las mujeres, pero no juzga a las demás. 
ellas se creen.
ellas se apoyan.
ellas se abrazan.
ellas saben que juntas son más fuertes.
ellas no se van a separar.
ellas somos nosotras y es el reflejo de esta ola feminista. 
estamos más unidas que nunca y entre todas vamos a luchar contra machismo. porque sí, todas y cada una de las mujeres de ese grupo abrazado y del mundo entero quieren dejar de vivir con miedo. .
.
.
.
.
.
(desconozco la ilustradora, si la conocen díganme el nombre para mencionarla, gracias).

text: been havin a pretty great time, lots of nice people & amazing views. switzerland has done a great job of keeping the old traditional style and incorporating modern. if you look at my stories from today you can see the beauty of lucerne, but if you go beneath the surface streets, theres a huge open modern train system complete with shops and restaurants. its seriously so tastefully done. i love being an american, its my thing, but i can’t imagine my country that i love so much doing anything this tasteful lol. 🤣🤣😅. its really so pretty here. the perfect balance of nature, history and modern life. 🇨🇭🐻#theoldladiesthattookthispicanddidntrunoffwithmyphone #switzerland

text:
van horn presents fuck your fear
conceived in #collaboration with @petersmesser this is „girl on girl painting 10“ by #bettytompkins #painting #art #exhibition . also included are works by
#judithbernstein #sophiecalle #gilbertandgeorge #zoeleonard #paulmccarthy #bjarnemelgaard #gregorschneider #cindysherman #wolfgangtillmans
opening fr. 18 jan. 2019

text:
in case you needed a reason to move to hawaii... on january 1, 2019 at the stroke of midnight, hawaii joined california and a few municipalities in new york to ban prospective employers from asking applicants about their prior salary history.  jurisdictions that have already passed similar laws that place restrictions on salary history during the application process include california, new york city, westchester, and suffolk county, new york. 
the new law, senate bill 2351, was signed by governor david y. ige on july 5, 2018. the relevant section states, in part, that “the legislature believes that the ability of employers to consider a job applicant’s previous salary history is a contributing factor to the gender pay disparity.” the section further cites new york city’s 2017 passage of similar legislation as a model to follow to “promote equality in the workplace and [to] close the pay gap between men and women.” read the full article here:  https://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/new-year-new-law-hawaii-s-ban-on-prior-83796/  #womeninsurfing #womengetpaid #womeninsports #nastywomen #genderequality #metoo #timesup #womensmarch #womenvote #womenswave #whyimarch #imarchfor #equality #womensrights #feminism #feminist #intersectionalfeminism #intersectional #futureisfemale #femaleempowerment #girlsrule #girlsruntheworld #girlboss #ladyboss #ovarygang #girlpower #grlpower #womensupportingwomen #surfergirl #surfergrl

text:
привет, понедельник! пока, безделье и оливье!
⠀
сегодня заглянем в collins dictionary)
⠀
metoo - имеет 3 значения , самое популярное - adjective, denoting a cultural movement that seeks to expose and eradicate predatory sexual behaviour, especially in the workplace
⠀
#metoo - популярный хештег, мгновенно распространившийся в социальных сетях в октябре 2017 года, подчёркивающий осуждение сексуального насилия и домогательств, получивший распространение в результате скандала и обвинений кинопродюсера харви вайнштейна. считается, что именно в этом смысле данная фраза впервые была использована общественным активистом тараной берк, а позднее была популяризована актрисой алиссой милано, которая предложила женщинам ставить лайк и делать перепост, чтобы поделиться своим печальным опытом.
⠀
в facebook хештег использовался более 4,7 миллионом человек в 12 миллионах сообщений в течение первых 24 часов.
⠀
менее популярные значения:
- noun - slang - a person who does something because someone else has done it - существительное - слэнг - человек, который поступает так, как другие, повторяет действие за кем-то;
⠀
- adjective - slang - seeking to achieve success by imitating another business or product - прилагательное - слэнг - жажда добиться успеха, копирую чужой бизнес или продукт, e.g. a me-too airline

text:
реакция на #живусмесячными

когда я начала этот флешмоб, то осознавала, что реакция будет разной и я могу нарваться на всякое. так и получилось.

три реакции, которые я отчетливо заметила, стал бы флешмоб масштабнее как #янебоюсьсказать или #metoo было бы ещё больше. в одном посте выскажу мнение на всё. 1- ты ноешь:
людям свойственно приписывать тексту дополнительные контексты, которые в нем не указанны. это нормально. когда я написала о своей боли, люди решили, что это нытье. хотя, казалось бы, в моем тексте не было ни одного слова с эмоциями или просьбой пожалеть меня, что напрямую можно проинтерпретировать как «нытье». но, люди есть люди, что поделать. 2- постановка диагноза:
ну что ещё можно сказать человеку, которая говорит о физической боли? только отправить к врачу и поставить диагноз. у меня вопрос. почему людям не приходит в голову, что я уже была у врача и знаю все свои диагнозы? они думают, что до их комментария я сама бы не сообразила проконсультироваться у врачини?
кроме этого, разве в посте хоть слово сказано про необходимость поговорить о врачах и лечении? нет. я совсем другу тему поднимаю. мне важно чтобы другие персоны, у которых есть опыт менструаций, написали про него и выразили то, что не могут выразить из-за закрытости темы. отчасти это все касается и медицины, ведь врачи_ни, тоже несут ответственность за то, как мы чувствуем себя в этом процессе. но это системный вопрос, а не лично мой. 3- ты делаешь вклад в демонизацию месячных:
мне предъявили, что разговорами про боль во время менструации, я поддерживаю штамп о «нормальности боли». я писала лишь про свой опыт, он у меня болезненный. я не против того, чтобы женщины лечили боли, не против того, чтобы говорили о безболезненных месячных. только за! я хочу, чтобы как можно больше людей узнало, что месячные бывают разными. я хочу, чтобы вы рассказали о своих месячных без страха и стыда. я мечтаю, чтобы мне перестали писать, что «месячные это интимно», потому что это обычный процесс жизнедеятельности. никто не говорит, что пот это интимно, что сопли это интимно… но если что-то выделяется из вагины, это сразу становится интимным и об этом нельзя говорить…
#окейсоби #фемсоби

stop_filter_tweet: реакция на ивусмесячными когда я начала этот флешмоб , то осознавала , что реакция будет разной и я могу нарваться на всякое . так и получилось . три реакции , которые я отчетливо заметила , стал бы флешмоб масштабнее как или было бы ещё больше . в одном посте выскажу мнение на всё . 1- ты ноешь : людям свойственно приписывать тексту дополнительные контексты , которые в нем не указанны . это нормально . когда я написала о своей боли , люди решили , что это нытье . хотя , казалось бы , в моем тексте не было ни одного слова с эмоциями или просьбой пожалеть меня , что напрямую можно проинтерпретировать как « нытье » . но , люди есть люди , что поделать . 2- постановка диагноза : ну что ещё можно сказать человеку , которая говорит о физической боли ? только отправить к врачу и поставить диагноз . у меня вопрос . почему людям не приходит в голову , что я уже была у врача и знаю все свои диагнозы ? они думают , что до их комментария я сама бы не сообразила проконсультироваться у врачини ? кроме этого , разве в посте хоть слово сказано про необходимость поговорить о врачах и лечении ? нет . я совсем другу тему поднимаю . мне важно чтобы другие персоны , у которых есть опыт менструаций , написали про него и выразили то , что не могут выразить из-за закрытости темы . отчасти это все касается и медицины , ведь врачи_ни , тоже несут ответственность за то , как мы чувствуем себя в этом процессе . но это системный вопрос , а не лично мой . 3- ты делаешь вклад в демонизацию месячных : мне предъявили , что разговорами про боль во время менструации , я поддерживаю штамп о « нормальности боли » . я писала лишь про свой опыт , он у меня болезненный . я не против того , чтобы женщины лечили боли , не против того , чтобы говорили о безболезненных месячных . только за ! я хочу , чтобы как можно больше людей узнало , что месячные бывают разными . я хочу , чтобы вы рассказали о своих месячных без страха и стыда . я мечтаю , чтобы мне перестали писать , что « месячные это интимно » , потому что это обычный процесс жизнедеятельности . никто не говорит , что пот это интимно , что сопли это интимно… но если что-то выделяется из вагины , это сразу становится интимным и об этом нельзя говорить…

text:
people are outraged about this picture because you don't get to opt in and out of activism because you wanted to be 'nice'. the point of activism is that you stand your ground, even when it's uncomfortable.

in her case, she gets paid for this shit then she must be willing to do the work required. she did a whole cover last year for cosmo where she was branded as an 'activist', so people have a right to be pissed off when she pulls a stunt like this (taking a picture with an alleged abuser), especially now with the #mute campaign in the air. we don't only get to choose who is outraged by (#survivingrkelly) as though there are predators around us that we protect.  also, she didn't say she was afraid to say no. had the photo not been on online or had people not been outraged by its existence, would she have 'cringed' with the people? the 'apology' seems more like damage control/pr to protect her beloved 'good girl' brand than anything else. "the only thing necessary for the triumph of evil is for good men to do nothing" edmund burke. there is a place for 'niceness', playing nice with an alleged abuser isn't one of those moments. she committed to speak for and represent people who can't do those things for themselves, you don't get to take that hat off when it suits you, its a fucking full-time job. as an activist, she needs to uphold that commitment in almost all aspects of her life (private and public). you need to pick a side and commit to it. 
#metoo #timesup #survivingarthur
#wokeproject

text:
my friend sexually assaulted me one year ago this weekend. it was the most horrific moment of my life, creating the most horrifying and darkest year i have ever lived. and in all that horror, i choose to celebrate the gift that i was given as a result of the trauma. 
i write this letter to you. 
you stripped me down to nothing but a lifeless, soulless, empty vessel, but somehow my heart remained beating, it was a shallow beat, but it was there. 
through your inconceivable action when you felt that you love and adored me and wanted every piece of me, without my permission, in a snap of fingers, poof, goodbye jennalee. but my heart remained beating. 
i couldn’t feel, i couldn’t smile, i couldn’t touch or be touched, and this went on and on and on, but my heart remained beating. 
when i had multiple breakdowns and ended up on medication, contemplated at least 5 times or more over the first 7 mths, if i should continue to live or not, somehow my heart remained beating. 
when adam would remind me he was there for me in whatever way i needed, no matter what was happing in our world, my heart would beat a little more. 
when i drank night after night for months on end so i could laugh and feel free, happy and normal, but would often cry in a bathroom as all the personal judgment came flowing at me, if i didn’t pass out first, my heart remained beating, even if it didn’t want to. 
when my little girls smiled at me and told me how much they loved me and missed me, and didn’t want me to be sick anymore, my heart would beat a little stronger. 
and then when i would be triggered and reminded of what you did to me, it would slow again, but it remained beating. 
i lost people in my life that didn’t understand the way i was now or didn’t know how to be around me, it was okay, i understood, my heart remained beating. 
with each new beautiful soul that came into my life, and accepted me as i was, my heart beat even more. 
and with each time over the year i was triggered my heart remained beating, and with each beat it would get stronger and stronger. i told you, you could not bury me alive. my seed had been planted and that i wold grow into a big oak tree. 
more below...

as we are.  knowing ourselves, eachother, our world, respecting boundaries and limits without forcing beliefs to degrade freedoms of the whole jam. it's inhibiting, and rude habitat to base opinion, judgement, critique, and depleat resources to continue to degrade people equally human, if not sometimes actually more humane to others, for how they were born naturally. in the movement, i respect lgbt, maybe you were born that way, i don't expect you to change. it's cool, your rights matter. your right to love is right. i personally consider the rights to live and breathe, a better place to start. that's how i see it, start with a solid base, on children, women and minorities, accomplish and push for rights to love. its important, although, that's how you present yourself, and represent how you prefer to be loved, that's not a priority over representing lives. maybe help get active in ours too. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors #lgbtq

text:
protein treatments are designed to create a protective barrier for your hair. the additional proteins grab onto the hair follicle and fill any holes or gaps within the cuticle.

the result is stronger hair that has an extra layer of protection from damaging elements. it also looks and feels healthier.

it is only a temporary fix, however. that is why regular protein treatments are recommended, though it's also important not to go overboard. when paired with deep conditioning, the protein treatments can become an important part of maintaining or restoring healthy hair.

protein treatments do help maintain strong tresses, but they should be used sparingly. the ingredients that strengthen your hair and fill in cuticle gaps can also dry it out. overdoing it on the protein—especially while not applying enough moisture in the form of regular, deep conditioning—can lead to brittle hair.

you should always follow up protein treatments with moisturizing conditioners, preferably a deep conditioning treatment.

text:
to reclaim. to retrieve something previously lost, given or something that was taken. misogyny has been cemented into place using many tools. words are just one. today is about reclamation. today i reclaim the word "bitch". the same characteristics that if possessed by a man make him assertive, ambitious, confident make me, a woman...a bitch. a mark of shame to be borne by women if they ever dare succeed in business or in the workplace. this is a reminder that those ideologies still exist...and as long as they do, i'll continue to turn negative labels into positives by embracing them. if you wanna call me a bitch for pursuing my dreams, that's cool. i'm gonna own it by being the baddest bitch there ever was. peace.

text:
no trial yet but the music industry sucks as does those who give ignorance a platform...... mystikal could be walking out of jail as early as next week if everything goes to plan. according to a report from tmz today (jan. 13), a combination of funds from friends and a new record deal could lead to his release from caddo correctional center. the release would come before his trial for first degree rape and second-degree kidnapping starts this spring.

the rapper's attorney, joel pearce, told the celebrity news outlet that his client's friends and family have been raising money for his $3 million bond, but it was a newly-signed record deal that really helped him reach his goal.

according to tim yazbeck, another lawyer for the embattled rhymer, his new deal consists of him recording three unreleased albums. he's hoping to get an advance within days. mystikal's legal team is confident that the rapper can post bail and be released by the end of next week.

the ghetto fabulous artist has been behind bars since august 2017, after an unnamed woman accused both him and another man, averweone darnell holman, of raping her in may 2017. the alleged rape took place in october 2016. ( faces the same charges. a third person, a woman named tenichia monieck wafford, has also been charged with obstruction of justice in relation to the alleged assault for reportedly trying to persuade the woman to recant her story.

mystikal, whose real name is michael tyler, has denied all rape allegations against him. his lawyer believes the entire situation was fueled by the #metoo movement, which has exposed sexual misconduct by male executives and celebrities in the film and music industry.

mystikal’s rape trial is expected to start in may.

text:
"i am one"
today i looked in the mirror & reflected on all that i been through in life...from sexual abuse & rape, sickness, death, sleepless nights, worry, disappointments & so much more that i saw how each trial seem to separate me fom who i  really am...but when i looked closer i also saw that even though in this life i may have many trials & tribulations that as long as i keep my faith in christ jesus that still "i am one" in him. 
so each devastated piece of me comes together as one in him with a smile that bears witness to his love for all of me. so next time you look in the mirror & all you see is the broken pieces of yourself...i challenge you to look closer & recognize that you too are one in him 🙌🙌🙌🙌

text:
of the several female artists that continue to hold their own, here are some highlights:

etana has produced above average music for at least the past 10 years. she earned a nomination for best reggae album at the upcoming 61st annual grammy awards for her latest project, reggae forever. she is the first female nominee in that category since sister carol in 1997, and the fourth ever.

spice became the first reggae artist to cross the 1 million followers mark on instagram. known for raunchy lyrics, she ventured into social commentary on her single “black hypocrisy.” the song, which tackles the issue of colorism is on her billboard chart-topping mixtape entitled “captured.” i hope that spice tackles more serious issues in the future. she can be a positive influence for young women the way she is controlling the media right now.

queen ifrica has wowed audiences at festivals like rebel salute and #reggaesumfest for the past several years. her songs have broached the toughest topics from incest to skin bleaching. she sings out against crime, unhealthy diets, corruption, and other evils. queen ifrica is also well-rounded and able to discuss love and sexuality in tasteful ways.

leaders of the new school:

reggae revivalist jah9 is as refreshing as she is an enigmatic force. she’s a yoga practitioner and poet turned reggae performing artist. her dancehall career was nurtured by rorystonelove who produced her debut album. jah9’s lyrics are deep, thought-provoking, and meaningful. her music is powerful yet diverse.

the 17-year-old singer, songwriter, and guitarist, koffee, emerged as a star in 2018. her single’s, “burning,” and “raggamuffin,” gained local and international attention. look out for her new hit, “toast,” which looks to be an even bigger smash.

lila ike is one of the protege’s of grammy-nominated reggae revival leader protoje. she was a unique style and flair with songs about love and socioeconomic topics.

twenty-one-year-old yanah is known as “the tiny powerhouse.” with a hand-full of songs released to date, she has captivated listeners. her delivery is sultry and passionate. cont in the comments... #musicpodcast #podcasts #reggaetalk

text:
i've always been "small" or skinny. i never felt good in my body. always picked on for being too tall, or too lanky, ilooked like a praying mantis or a giraffe. my maternal grandfather and my sperm donor were both tall, thin men, its genetic obviously, and yet even my own "family" members have accused me of having a eating disorder. (first 2 pics)

2017 was probably the worst year of my life and i do not say that lightly. i was in an extremely unhealthy and unsafe relationship. i became someone i never wanted to be in order to survive. i did things i, as who i am in my heart, at my core, would never do. and yet, i was still on the verge of death. love can be so beautiful and warm, safe, fulfilling. but also be cold, hurtful, maddening and blinding. especially when its already isolated you from everyone and everything you love, everything that makes you, so beautifully you. and then you don't notice until it's too late.. or so you think. (next 2 pics was me when i walked away the first time)

2017 nearly killed me, but it also saved my life. it showed me that i needed 2 love myself. that i needed 2 accept myself. that i needed 2 respect myself. i couldn't look myself in the mirror and say "i love you"...today i feel the most absolute best in my body n about who i am, than i have ever felt before! i feel confident and healthy. i am confident and healthy! my sexiness, my womanness can only go up from here!! to the world i say this "to everyone who has ever felt like they were in the wrong body, that it didnt feel right to them, to every person who's ever been in an abusive or just unhealthy relationship and you dont see the way out, to every person who's ever been ashamed of who you are... you are beautiful! every scar, every mole, every curve, every type of hair, every skin color, every gender, every sexual preference...you are beautiful in every aspect of you! believe in yourself. surround yourself with people who also believe in you so they can lift you up on those days you wanna give up. fuck it, reach out to me and i will build you up! i got you. because you got you! peace. love. and light sistahs and brothas✌🏾 #selfcare #selflove #respect #believe #love

text:
some people ask me what it’s like coming out of a cult.  well, here’s the honest truth:⁣
⁣
one day you feel completely empowered.  you are cruising down the highway with your freedom songs blasting away, singing your heart out, and feeling invincible. ⁣
⁣
the next morning you are crumpled in a heap on your bedroom floor, gasping for breath, desperately wondering how you’re going to make it even one more day.⁣
⁣
that’s what my life has been like. ⁣
⁣
but i’ll tell you what i’ve also learned:⁣
⁣
even the worst day in freedom is better than the best day in bondage.  freedom often terrifying, when your place of bondage appears so much more secure. ⁣
⁣
embrace your freedom in christ, your freedom in life.  embrace the tears, the laughter, the joy and the grief.  you don’t have to hold on to jesus, because he’s holding on to you.  you don’t have to fight for your freedom, for he’s the one fighting for you.⁣
⁣
rest, dear friend. ⁣
⁣
rest in his sanctuary.  rest in his hope.  rest in his peace. ⁣
⁣
rest in being enough.⁣
⁣
#hope #peace #enough #jesus #cult #survivor #metoo #churchtoo #freedom #joy
name: Finding God’s Gifts

text:
прочла последний роман виктора пелевина «тайные виды на гору фудзи». ощущения странные: будто долго жевала что-то противное, а послевкусие оказалось приятным. 
олигарх скучает на яхте и задумывается о том, что счастья он так и не достиг. и для решения этой проблемы привлекает стартап из сколкова, а те - буддийских монахов для достижения олигархом просветления. 
иронизировать над олигархами так же актуально, как рассказывать анекдот: «встретились русский, еврей и татарин...» кстати, олигархов в книге действительно трое, и они именно этих национальностей. вообще, слово «олигарх» откуда-то из 2000-х. но есть в книге и более актуальная лексика: часто упоминаются илон маск, фейсбук, движение #metoo. к нему примыкает бывшая содержанка и по совместительству бывшая одноклассница олигарха. выйдя в тираж (в силу возраста), она вдруг запоздало чувствует себя оскорбленной мужчинами. 
пересказывать пелевина невозможно, это как пытаться повторить вслух дурацкий сон. но если отбросить странный сюжет, в сухом остатке будет жесткий и справедливый вывод о нашем времени.

цитаты: 🖊
«деньги - это наркотик, на который сегодня с младенчества сажают всех».
🖊
«современный человек лжёт в среднем пятьдесят раз в день без каких-либо специальных усилий. разумеется, для топ-менеджеров и крупных бизнесменов эта цифра значительно выше».
🖊
«самое ужасное, что наевшийся пустых слов человек, начинает верить будто постиг что-то важное. а ему просто добавили мусора в голову».

text:
the feelings get to you and change you. perception is altered and messes begin in places you never visit again. only memories stick and you wish you could erase the damage with a simple tearful blink. i have a home now. i am content in the warm glow that i’ve created within my nest. while the worst has gripped me, i am able to release myself from its madness and leave it in the dirty, deep black blanket that covers the emptiness i hide from inside.
