text:
watching ice cream melt, waiting for the children: more time to think. a summer's tale: chapter 6.
"shaz. can you get that bleeder for me."
it was surgery day for jerome, and there were 6 male cats waiting to be desexed.
"as i always say, 'you can't beat a castrated male as a perfect companion!'" sharon had an urge to stab him with the scalpel. she had heard this joke for mths and was over it. she was waiting for the reverse #metoo movement to start so she could secretly out him, but there didn't seem to be much interested.
"shaz. another bleed. grab it will you?. thanks." he dropped the severed testicle into the bin, and continued, "did you here bout the westies in the car with that dead fellow?" sharon was busy trying to work out where the sudden sea of blood was coming from. finally she located the bleeding vessel, clamped it off, and using a handful of guaze swabs removed the excess blood. the second testicle was now in plain view. "i read that there were 2 great danes in the car, and they were guarding the body," said sharon.
"i haven't read this morning news read. what else have they said?"
"they had trouble getting the body away from one of the dogs and had to shoot it..."
"they reported that in the news feed?"
"what?" sharon asked. "that they had to shoot the dog. i'm surprised the police released that bit of information "
"they didn't. the reporter quoted, 'unnamed sources.'"
"any comment from the police?"
"only 'no comment'" replied sharon
"they always close ranks when there is a shooting," commented jerome.
with that he felt his phone vibrate in his pocket.

who was trying to contact jerome? 
all will be revealed in the next chapter of 'a summer's tale'
name: Dr Rod Graham - Village Vet

text:
remembering the #womensmarch #berlin in 2017 and 18 month old daughter, the most peaceful protester. i’m still so inspired by this movement and #metoo, even though subsequent events have shown we still have a lot of work ahead. this saturday, january 19, 2019, i’ll also be bringing my daughter and now my my 8 month old son for the #womensmarchberlin at #brandenburg gate.

let me know if you’ll be there too! in the evening i’ll be reading at the wicked poetry slam a selection on difference and the potential for bridging and understanding in our communities.

text:
s w i p e 👈🏼 | 2009-2019. ⁣
i was 16 in this photo. + when i look at it, i remember how insanely obsessed i was with crazy hair. with winged liner. with paramore. with tech n9ne. with beer pong. with tequila. i had the most amazing group of friends that i trusted with my life. + only a few knew my truth. ⁣
⁣
that a couple years prior, i had been in an incredibly abusive relationship with a boy for almost a year. who used me to work his anger out on. who would hurt me in places where the world couldn’t see. who threatened my life if i told. + being 15 years old, of course i believed it. ⁣
⁣
i remember keeping a bottle of vodka tucked away in the bottom of my dresser. i’d sneak drinks before school. if i even had energy to even go that day. most days i’d lay in bed. sneaking drinks to keep the numbness but coherent enough to talk to my parents. ⁣
⁣
on the outside, i looked perfectly happy. i was witty, + still a smart ass. i had an amazing boyfriend away at college. but i was drowning. by this time in 2009, i had dropped out of my senior year. moved to a different town. + desperately trying to keep my nightmares at bay. ⁣
⁣
when i couldn’t find a drink i would slip into withdrawals. my parents + siblings could see me slipping + were worried, but what could they do? one night after i had drank a little too much i finally told my mom about what happened. + it was like the dam released. ⁣
⁣
but i couldn’t stop drinking.⁣
⁣
eventually my brother + sister intervened. they made the decision to move me out to texas to live with my brother + his family. they saved my life.⁣
⁣
i look back on this picture now + i can smile because although i went through hell, i’m hella stronger. ⁣
not all from that time are harsh memories + i choose to see the good instead. ⁣
⁣
now, ten years later, i’m 27 + i’m alive.⁣
i have the most amazing little family i couldn’t have even dreamed of. ⁣
i have the most amazing husband. ⁣
+ i will be 8 years sober this year + i am damn proud of it. ⁣
⁣
if you are going or have gone through something similar, please, do. not. stay. silent. ⁣
you are worth everything. ⁣
+ you deserve everything. ⁣
know that you are not alone. ⁣
+ that you are so loved. 🖤

eventually my brother + sister intervened. they made the decision to move me out to texas to live with my brother + his family. they saved my life.⁣
⁣
i look back on this picture now + i can smile because although i went through hell, i’m hella stronger. ⁣
not all from that time are harsh memories + i choose to see the good instead. ⁣
⁣
now, ten years later, i’m 27 + i’m alive.⁣
i have the most amazing little family i couldn’t have even dreamed of. ⁣
i have the most amazing husband. ⁣
+ i will be 8 years sober this year + i am damn proud of it. ⁣
⁣
if you are going or have gone through something similar, please, do. not. stay. silent. ⁣
you are woh everything. ⁣
+ you deserve everything. ⁣
know that you are not alone. ⁣
+ that you are so loved. 🖤

text:
quyền lực mới (đặt mua trước - giảm ngay 30%)
đặt mua tại http://bit.ly/datmuaquyenlucmoi

không thể phủ nhận rằng đang có một làn sóng dịch chuyển rất lớn trong nhu cầu của con người. từ việc chỉ quan tâm đến những yếu tố cơ bản của đời sống như ăn mặc, chỗ ở... những cá nhân đơn lẻ đang khao khát cất tiếng nói và dần tụ họp lại với nhau để hình thành những cộng đồng lớn mạnh lan tỏa lý tưởng của họ. xu hướng này mở ra một thế giới mới, nơi chứa đựng những xung đột quyết liệt giữa hệ thống quyền lực cũ và cái gọi là “quyền lực mới”. cuốn sách quyền lực mới của hai tác giả jeremy heimans và henry timms, chỉ với hơn 300 trang, đã nhận diện sự trỗi dậy của dạng quyền lực này như một hệ thống đang định hình thế giới tương lai của chúng ta.

có thể xem quyền lực cũ là một cơ chế áp đặt quyền lực, nguồn lực từ trên xuống như những định chế chính trị, đoàn thể và được kiểm soát chỉ bởi một hoặc một vài cá nhân. trong khi đó, quyền lực mới lại đòi hỏi mọi người tham gia, chia sẻ những ý tưởng, nhờ đó hình thành một cộng đồng có cùng tiếng nói với quyền lực được chia sẻ ngang bằng nhau. quyền lực mới đang tạo ra những “cú nổ” trong nhiều lĩnh vực. đây chính là lý do nền kinh tế ngày nay là sân chơi của các doanh nghiệp chia sẻ như airbnb, uber… nền chính trị hiện nay bị chao đảo bởi hàng loạt phong trào phản kháng nổi lên từ mạng xã hội như #metoo, black lives matter... và những nền tảng giáo dục như ted talks, coursera... có thể thu hút hàng chục triệu người tham gia.

với cuốn sách quyền lực mới, hai tác giả không chỉ đề cập đến câu chuyện quyền lực trong thế giới ngày nay ở lĩnh vực công nghệ, kinh tế, chính trị mà còn giúp mỗi người đọc mở ra hướng tư duy mới về khả năng của chính mình trong việc đóng góp cho cộng đồng. làm thế nào để bạn tạo ra những ý tưởng mà cộng đồng sẽ chung tay để nó lớn mạnh và lan tỏa? làm sao để bạn tạo ra một tổ chức bền vững trong kỷ nguyên mà các mối liên hệ trở nên tạm bợ và lỏng lẻo? những trang sách của quyền lực mới sẽ chia sẻ cách mà những phong trào toàn cầu đang tạo ra một thế giới ngày càng tốt đẹp hơn.

#sachmoi #sachdattruoc #quyenlucmoi #newpower #firstnewstriviet

với cuốn sách quyền lực mới, hai tác giả không chỉ đề cập đến câu chuyện quyền lực trong thế giới ngày nay ở lĩnh vực công nghệ, kinh tế, chính trị mà còn giúp mỗi người đọc mở ra hướng tư duy mới về khả năng của chính mình trong việc đóng góp cho cộng đồng. làm thế nào để bạn tạo ra những ý tưởng mà cộng đồng sẽ chung tay để nó lớn mạnh và lan tỏa? làm sao để bạn tạo ra một tổ chức bền vững trong kỷ nguyên mà các mối liên hệ trở nên tạm bợ và lỏng lẻo? những trang sách của quyền lực mới sẽ chia sẻ cách mà những phong trào toàn cầu đang tạo ra một thế giới ngày càng tốt đẹp hơn.

#sachmoi #sachdattruoc #quyenlucmoi #newpower #firstnewstriviet

text:
gratitude george, u r a life saver.
because of u my sweet dog, my tender constant companion, my canine love...
i am still alive.
the alpha of 2019 has been a colossal fiasco. my detested demon depression has reared its ugly head once again.
so here goes - a genesis of posts about my story. 
shall i call it “living with a killer?” absolutely. because thats what it is!
the #1 cause of disability in the world is depression. 
suicide is the #2 cause of death in 15-29 year olds.
i know there’s a profound number of u out there who suffer from this dreadful illness. i vow to bare my soul so that others who r silently suffering will b heard. 
chances r, if u don’t have it, 
u don’t really get it.
chances r if u know someone w/it,
u understand it better, & chances r if you’ve lost someone from suicide, 
u r traumatized, but still don’t truly fathom why a person would choose to end their life.
(imagine depression as the pain of drowning in a scalding vat of boiling oil)
now is the time to explain wtf this demon does to a person from firsthand knowledge.
i hope to god this post makes whoever reads it more hopeful, understanding, & educated in something unthinkably heinous.
but most of all, to u in agony, u r not alone thinking about death as a way out. 
this candor may upset many people but that’s tough. i’m writing this not to make friends, but to save lives!
my 1st piece of advice to my fellow depression brethren;
get as close to a dog as possible. if u r able to adopt a dog, run don’t walk.... i’m partial to dogs for depression, please no hate from cat lovers. i loved & had 7 cats at one time but they didn’t help me as much as a 1 dog. 
i adopted george from @dogswithoutborders & think they 
r incredible af. 
please - if u can pick up the phone & call 1 person u suspect is sad/depressed then do it asap. better yet, if possible hug them.
i pray to god this reaches as many people as possible.
if u could post comments this would b incredibly appreciated.
with all the #love in my heart, & as much #hope as i can muster, carlye 
#depressionawareness #ptsd #sadness #understanding #suicideprevention #metoo #kindness #death #pain #pray 
#dogadoption #emotional #support
name: carlyeclapton

text:
i finished watching "surviving r. kelly". i was pretty young when allegations started coming out about r. kelly to really understand what was going on but i'm a grown woman now and i get it.
•
•
i understand that women of all races are affected by rape and mental and physical abuse including men but right now this is about a community of black girls and people are blaming them, calling them "fast girls", "where were there parents", "why are these girls not leaving" or still making jokes about this and flat out remaining to believe this man is innocent. that's your prerogative but it's also saying a big "fuck you" to these girls; it's like saying and i have heard from people point blank that it was these girls faults. do you know how it feels to be so scared of letting your family down, scared of the things these predators may go after your family or the humiliation and guilt you feel.
•
•
these girls were little girls and were brainwashed for years. so when people say "why did these women stay why did they not tell there parents or why didn't they go after r. kelly" first of all some of these girls did not have parents to defend them and brainwashing is a real thing. plus they were little girls! a grown man with all this money and fame promising young girls fame and fortune, only to be treated like animals, raped and abused and turned away from those who did have caring parents. my heart breaks for these girls/women and for the families involved and with out there daughters. i pray that some kind of justice is served for these victims/survivors and that maybe people will start listening and put this monster away so he can not ruin anymore lives.
•
•

text:
#touchmenot #metoo a great way to end one of the most difficult semesters. thank you to everyone who came out and supported the films! “90% of sexual assaults on college campuses go unreported”
for those who might have missed it, my film “touch me not” is about sexual assault on college campuses. after to speaking to many girls in my school and i realized that many of us had similar stories, and no one reported their assault. i wanted to bring attention to the severity of assault on college campuses. as difficult as it was to work on such a triggering subject i’m proud of the film and everyone who worked on it. my crew was amazing and understanding of the importance of the topic, as we are all advocates for the metoo movement as we step closer to the world of hollywood. i’m forever grateful for my cast and crew. thank you to my professors and parents as well for all their support.

text:
for those who don’t know, surviving r. kelly is a documentary revolved around the lifestyle of r. kelly during his years of fame and there have been many women, survivors who have shared their stories during their time with kelly. he was abusive, both sexually and mentally. there have been many women, black women who have spoken out during this time to reveal what kelly was really like, a monster. for many years, these women have tried their best to reach out and make these claims against him, but unfortunately they weren’t heard, and also because of the obvious fact that they’re black. finally, after some time, they shed light on these women and they slowly began to bring kelly down. during this time, about 27% of phone calls aired to the national sexual assault hotline, which is incredible. within the three of us, and hopefully many, many more of you to follow, we stand 100% behind any women who have experienced sexual assault, sexual abuse, rape, sexual misconduct, etc. and we believe you. nobody deserves to go through any of this, and the fact that these women are black speaks volumes. this isn’t fair to them, or anyone who has tried really hard for their voice to be heard, but have gotten denied. 
#thisisnotconsent #webelieveher #metoo #metoomovement #muterkelly #beyou #befearless #fearlessbc

text:
bless the thing that broke you down and cracked you wide open, because the world needs you open. // rebecca campbell

everyone has that thing that broke you.  that thing that created a before and after.  that thing that has caused great suffering, yet has allowed you to heal in ways you never knew you were capable.  when we let go of that pain that has controlled us for so long, you begin to realize your strength even in all those raw and broken places.

you rise past it and you can live the life you deserve.

week two: yoga for depression

come join us in the third and final week, next sunday.  as we explore how to find compassion yourself through yoga.

www.swanriverarabi.com

everyone has that thing that broke you.  that thing that created a before and after.  that thing that has caused great suffering, yet has allowed you to heal in ways you never knew you were capable.  when we let go of that pain that has controlled us for so long, you begin to realize your strength even in all those raw and broken places.

you rise past it and you can live the life you deserve.

week two: yoga for depression

come join us in the third and final week, next sunday.  as we explore how to find compassion yourself through yoga.

www.swanriverarabi.com

.
true power need not shout from the rooftops.  need not dominate or control or shame others to feel alive.  it originates inside.  it is quiet yet it’s ferocity and capacity to mobilize when necessary is unmistakable.
.
in the wake of the #metoo movement and the unspeakable “power” abuses that we are inundated with every single day— how do we begin to shift the energy in our own bodies, relationships and communities in a way that :::doesn’t::: replicate the exploitation and abuse that got us into this mess in the first place...?
.
in a way that is deep, lasting and sustainable—
.
if you are tired of waiting for someone to hand you your freedom... of asking for :::permission::: to have a voice... of cowering in the face of chaos and uncertainty... of sitting on your gifts and talents and unique contribution for a world on the verge of a :::massive::: renaissance, i hope that you will join us for this free class this wednesday 16th january @ 2p pst 💥 .
.

.

text:
hi guys. so here it is. this is me. some chub, pale skin, self harm, veins, stretch marks, cellulite, everything. i bet there are a few more things i can point out that no one else notices but me. i really am passionate about making this a community for people. i figure there’s no better way to show my commitment and drive than to show me. all the flaws that photoshop and good angles take out of the photos. though i usually stay away from altering my body, and have a history of keeping away from makeup, i felt like this would be the real starting line for this page, and for me and my own growing confidence and self love. if i can’t learn to love my body, then how can i learn to love everything else about me. why would people trust that i think they’re beautiful if i don’t even think it about myself and all my own “flaws”? here is to me being real. 
ps. i know a lot of the time we look at other girls online saying that they are self conscious but we look at them and say “ya right you’re beautiful and you know it”. so 1. everyone has insecurities, never bring anyone down for it. 
2. i hope seeing a body like mine, different from what we normally see, gives you any inspiration or spark that you needed.
keep loving ❤️💕
.
.
#selflove #thisisme #realbodies #cellulite #curves #nofilter #selfharm #stretchmarks #beautiful #me #metoo #everyonematters #buzzedhead #insecure #pleaselook #share

text:
hot news
sutradara film sanju, rajkumar hirani tersandung masalah pelecehan seksual 😯

tahun 2019 tampaknya belum berakhir yang menyangkut terkait kasus pelecehan seksual. meskipun telah melihat cukup banyak nama yang diciptakan oleh gerakan #metoo, nama terbaru yakni pembuat film rajkumar hirani pasti mengejutkan satu bollywood. terlepas dari orang-orang di media sosial, selebritis seperti vinta nanda juga menyatakan ketidakpercayaannya pada pembuat film berkelas ini yang dituduh melakukan pelanggaran seksual. 
yang terakhir bereaksi sama adalah aktris amardeep jha. amardeep jha baru-baru ini membuka suara tentang pengalaman dirinya bekerja dengan rajkumar hirani. menurut laporan media, amardeep mengatakan bahwa di lokasi syuting, rajkumar hirani bahkan seperti malaikat berjalan. menurut apa yang amardeep ketahui tentang sang sutradara secara pribadi, berita ini pasti mengejutkan dia.

berbicara tentang tuduhan yang ditujukan kepada rajkumar hirani, mengatakan bahwa meskipun rajkumar tidak dapat menghakimi gadis itu, dia secara pribadi merasa bahwa rajkumar tidak dapat melakukan pelecehan itu. rajkumar bahkan tidak pernah memberikan komentar cabul atau membuat lelucon kasar di lokasi syuting.

menurut laporan media, asisten direktur rajkumar hirani dari film sanju telah menuduh pembuat film itu melakukan pelecehan seksual padanya lebih dari satu kali. wanita itu bahkan mengirim surat tentang hal yang sama kepada rajkumar hirani dan rekan-rekannya yang termasuk vidhu vinod chopra dan istrinya anupama chopra.

rajkumar hirani baru-baru ini merilis pernyataan yang menyangkal semua tuduhan yang ditujukan kepadanya. dia mengatakan dalam pernyataan itu, “saya benar-benar terkejut ketika tuduhan ini diajukan kepada saya sekitar dua bulan yang lalu. saya segera menyarankan bahwa penting untuk membawa masalah ini ke komite atau badan hukum mana pun. pengadu memilih untuk pergi ke media sebagai gantinya. saya ingin menyatakan dengan sangat kuat bahwa ini adalah cerita jahat yang salah dan nakal yang disebarkan dengan tujuan menghancurkan reputasi saya”. 😯

#timesofindia
@rajkumarhiranifilms @hirani.rajkumar #amardeepjha #vidhuvinodchopra #sanju #metoo

no one owns my story
besides me. -mahriyah willow

a series. .

power and sex.
when you touch me
and i have said no
you take power
away from me. 
if i say yes,
because i am afraid 
or feel guilty
you take power 
away from me. -mahriyah willow

sex loses meaning after each time. eventually, i believed each person was allowed to take from me what they wanted. i felt hurt and ugly when they did not 'want' me.
.
.
.
you make me laugh and 
seem so sweet.
you are being kind so - 
what do i have 
to offer you?
the same thing they all wanted...
.
.
yet now you say 
that i am too easy,
what is it then? 
am i a slut or 
am i a tease...
because they both 
make me feel
wrong. -mahriyah willow
.
.
.
.

text:
words for the world:
me too part 10.
a series. .
.
.
why you wanted me
i never knew
felt like i was broken
until you told me
hold your head up high
you are not your past
and we are going somewhere fast. .
.
.
gentle kisses on my forhead,
tender whispers in my ear.
with you i feel what i
have not felt before.
friendship first
and so much patience.
you saw me at my worst
before you ever got my best.
i know we are lucky
for having what we do,
that you have been through
so much too. 
thank you for 
never being mad 
that sometimes i shrink 
away from you,
fearing not you
but those that came before.
know that i appreciate
each time you wipe my tears
and assure me that 
one day i will feel 
like me again.
your love has been my
little caccoon -
keeping me warm during
my layers of healing. 
i can't wait till the day
my mind clears up
and my body trusts,
when it will be just
you and i.
♡♡ -mahriyah willow
.
.
.
.

text:
words for the world:
me too part 11.
a series. .
the end.. for now
.
ask yourself
"does this feel right?" if you get a pit
it most certainly isn't
.
maybe as we grow
we learn not everything 
can be defined by
the limited exposures 
of our childhood. .
.
.
i look out.
now i am grown.
that little girl inside -
she asks me how 
i could have let
myself be hurt this way
she asks me why i lied 
to myself
over and over and over,
in the hopes of acceptance
from a world that 
turns a blind eye
to the terror it 
perpetuates.
saying things like 
what did you wear?
did you drink too much?
well boys just cant 
help themselves. 
world. 
you make me 
sick. 
for i am only now seeing
all the abuse that was
inflicted on me -
what you call a
social justice warrior
is a hero to me. 
too many times
i thought it was all 
my fault and that i 
deserved it. 
after all -
i always gave it up. 
i didnt know.. they could have stopped. -mahriyah willow
.
.
.
.

text: after being told he would get a 24 hour notice before she would get released, he deemed it safe to let his mother-in-law help watch his son when he worked. see this helped me out too because at that time i had a two year old and an 8month old, and i watch the baby while my brother works. our whole family was against the idea of her family helping out at all until a custody order was in place, but after being told by two different sources that we would in fact get a 24 hour notice before she would be released, my brother deemed it safe to let his mother-in-law watch the baby while he worked. his mother-in-law bails her daughter out while watching the baby, and now they have custody because she is still the mother and no custody order is in place. the day this happened (july 16th, 2018) my brother did everything in his power to get his son back including calling the police and cys, nothing could be done. the only reason we even knew she was bailed out was i signed up for alerts from our county prison, to notify me of changes in the offenders status. which they notified me after she was already released. #domesticabuse #domesticviolence #emotionalabuse #abuse #domesticviolenceawareness #metoo #domesticviolencesurvivor #sociopath #narcissist #depressionandanxiety #narcissisticabusesurvivor #speakup #divorce #cptsd #emotionalabuse #abusiverelationships #victimblaming #abusiverelationship #abusedwomen #abusedmen #victimmentality #gaslighter #awareness #narcissisticabuse #gaslighting

text:
why did i leave ig? .
.
many people have been asking me so what did you do on your break from instagram. as if life in itself has to be done with instagram. it was my choice to separate to work on myself. now people keep asking me what does that mean which worries me. everyone says they need to work on themselves but then feel the need to ask others what “working on themselves means.” it’s up to you! whatever you feel you need to work on in your life the most than do it! eliminate all distractions, all excuses, all people, who aren’t aligned with what you want or where you are going. personally through this time off i’ve been able to become stronger emotionally, learn to accept myself while continuing to work on becoming better. i was very depressed and my mentality & actions weren’t something i wanted to share at the moment with others. in fact i rarely had any human contact with anyone at all. yes i exercised, yes i ate better, yes i slept more, yes i prayed more ... but it’s more of everything that i started to not do anymore that showed me my true growth as a person. i no longer have suicidal thoughts or self harm and i’ve been dealing with that for the past 6 years on and off. but these past few months i took time to heal. and let me tell you healing is such a beautiful thing. .
.
i have kept all the messages of the people who wrote to me the day i left the gram and i actually read them a lot throughout my time away. it’s amazing how words from people you don’t even know can truly lift you up at times . so please don’t underestimate the power of social media and using it to spread kindness. .
. 
i am happy, i am still working on myself but i value myself more than ever and it reflects completely with the people i choose to do life with. choose yourself first ❤️
#empwr 
#nataliezusel

why did i leave ig? .
.
many people have been asking me so what did you do on your break from instagram. as if life in itself has to be done with instagram. it was my choice to separate to work on myself. now people keep asking me what does that mean which worries me. everyone says they need to work on themselves but then feel the need to ask others what “working on themselves means.” it’s up to you! whatever you feel you need to work on in your life the most than do it! eliminate all distractions, all excuses, all people, who aren’t aligned with what you want or where you are going. personally through this time off i’ve been able to become stronger emotionally, learn to accept myself while continuing to work on becoming better. i was very depressed and my mentality & actions weren’t something i wanted to share at the moment with others. in fact i rarely had any human contact with anyone at all. yes i exercised, yes i ate better, yes i slept more, yes i prayed more ... but it’s more of everything that i started to not do anymore that showed me my true growth as a person. i no longer have suicidal thoughts or self harm and i’ve been dealing with that for the past 6 years on and off. but these past few months i took time to heal. and let me tell you healing is such a beautiful thing. .
.
i have kept all the messages of the people who wrote to me the day i left the gram and i actually read them a lot throughout my time away. it’s amazing how words from people you don’t even know can truly lift you up at times . so please don’t underestimate the power of social media and using it to spread kindness. .
. 
i am happy, i am still working on myself but i value myself more than ever and it reflects completely with the people i choose to do life with. choose yourself first ❤️
#empwr 
#nataliezusel

text:
for many many years i have dedicated my career and life to empowering, encouraging and inspiring young women, girls and children. in light of recent disturbing news and also because i have never met more people in my entire life who want to be famous, i am focused on solutions to help educate parents and keep young women, girls and children safe. i will be creating new video content sharing tips on how to not be scammed or taken advantage of, the importance of having a positive support system around you, and so much more. i have already talked to some of my professional female friends in the entertainment industry and we will be sharing our stories and giving advice we wish we had known or were told when we were younger. i am also looking into how i can expand my mentoring programs so a team and i can reach more girls and children who are not being protected. i believe all violators should continue to be exposed and have to answer to their crimes, survivors should continue speaking up and get the help they need when they are ready, and i believe we need to be proactive because it takes a village! 💋

text:
reading a feel good book is a great form of self care. for all my friends with fur babies.  you need to read this book… a dog’s way home is funny, sweet, and it will make you cry.  it’s a story of a dog’s love for her master and the bond that they share. i read this book first and then william and i read it together.  we related to that bond with our fur babies and enjoyed every page.  the story is told from the dog’s perspective and it’s just a sweet story.  have you read this book yet?  if not take a read and let me know your thoughts. i got this book for my birthday and i couldn’t put it down, i read it in less than a week. it was a feel good story. i think this is a book that all dog lovers will cherish.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#holisticliving #wellness #wellnessinsideout #agouldstory #fgnaturalwellness #selfcare #wellnesswednesday #metoo #healthyliving #healthyhome #healthyfamilies

text:
last week i started rehearsals for a show called “good friday”. and honestly i just wanted to show up on time and get my lines right. but this show demands and deserves more. for the first time as an asian american actor, i’ve been given the chance to play a character that is so beautifully complex, profoundly broken, and strips me completely bare. and i want you to be there.

i am so so fortunate to have a place at the table among this intelligent, luminous, and loving cast of makers. i can’t tell you how excited i am for this infinitely-layered, explosively courageous show. and you guys, it’s brimming with a gorgeous palette of characters of color. with rich inner lives. that transcend stereotypes. and aren’t there to fill your effing diversity quota. 
get your tickets now (link below + in bio) and please feel free to dm me if you have any questions. more updates to come!!
.
.
.

directed by sherri eden barber

tickets: http://theflea.org/shows/good-friday/ .

text: i hate the question “was he ever physically violent to you”? it’s as if emotional, sexual and financial abuse are no big deal. if he didn’t beat you up then what you complaining about?? coercive control. emotional abuse. mental manipulation. gaslighting. marital rape. sexual abuse. these are not “physical” in the way most people think of domestic violence. and in no way are they any less damaging and painful. sometimes they can be worse because the scars are on the inside. the wounds are in my heart. the bullets in my mind. the words trapped. invisible. #rape #violence #mentalhealthawareness #depression #itgetsbesser #metoo #maritalrape #sexualabuse #emotionalabuse #mentalabuse #abuse #domesticviolenceawareness #domesticabuse

text: i’ve always gotten a lot of unwanted attention. just this month i’ve gotten a lot of really creepy messages pertaining to my fitness/body. in the past, i’ve let these things deter me from my goals because of how self conscious it had made me. i’ve found myself time and time again hiding in a corner at the gym, avoiding public places, wearing oversized clothing, etc. the #metoo movement is very relevant to so many women and men. it’s acts like this that make the world, in my opinion, more ugly than it needs to be. this year i won’t let these creeps take my progress from me anymore. i’ve made a vow to myself to confront these people and not let it weigh so heavily on me. if you are one of these people i have described, then you need to change your ways because you’re nothing more than a creep and everything less. #fitness #empowerment #militarywomen

text:
estás ahí, acostada en una camilla ginecológica adentro de un sucio garage, estás nerviosa y no dejas de mirar la luz parpadeante.

lo único que hay ahí es una mesita con varios medicamentos y elementos medicos, una silla, la camilla en donde estás acostada y una vieja televisión apagada.

un hombre con una bata blanca entra en la sala y sin decir palabra alguna te inyecta algo que supones es anestesia, y mientras poco a poco te vas adormeciendo no podes evitar recordar como llegaste ahí.

era tu primera vez y tu pareja insistió aunque no estabas segura.

era tu primera vez y no conocías la existencia de la educación sexual integral.

era tu primera vez y tu pareja había sido educada por el porno.

era tu primera vez y él te dijo que con preservativo no sentía placer.

era tu primera vez y escuchaste por ahí que la primera vez no quedabas embarazada.

era tu primera vez y tu novio te dijo que si acababa afuera no pasaba nada.

era tu primera vez y él te acabó adentro aunque le dijiste que no.

era tu primera vez y te mintieron.

era tu primera vez y te la arruinaron.

era tu primera vez y terminaste acostada en el garage de un supuesto médico que te recomendó una amiga del barrio.

el pánico te invade, sabes que lo mas probable es que no vayas a sobrevivir, pero ya es tarde para arrepentirse, ya estás totalmente inconciente.

el proceso terminó, pero no sé si despertaste. lo único que sé con certeza, es que esa tarde el piso se manchó de sangre.

text:
rape is rape!! no means no!!! stop means stop!!! if i said those words and you still did what you did without my consent, it's rape!! here's my story: 
#whyididntreport #metoo
i was raped 7 times. they were all different. the 1st 4 were when i was 12 to 16. by 3 different guys. i told my family..but they didn't believe me. neither did the police. i thought i deserved it.
i was raped a year ago by a person close to me.  he was younger than me. 
it happened 3 different times in 3 different months. i didn't tell anyone until last october. a month after it happened. again, nobody believed me. 
i thought it was my fault because i should've known better. i was older. everyone said it wasn't rape because i was older and i didn't come out pregnant. i didn't go to the doctor at all. for either times. i felt like i was an embarrassement to my family. like,"wow, you're 18,he was 14, that's not considered rape" i told him to stop.  that's another reason why i didn't say anything.
i told myself "i should've spoke up sooner. i just don't want to be judged." but i was. i was called names like, (excuse my language) slut and whore. 
it really hurt me. i got so depressed. i started to question god. i blamed it on him. it wasn't right. i thought he was punishing me. i couldn't eat, i couldn't sleep. i started to question everyone in my life...seeing if they would do the same thing or judge me for it. i pushed people away.. and learned to hide my feelings. i would fake smile and say i was fine. i eventually lost my faith...but i got it back❤️ but i forgave those people who hurt me. it's still hard to this day. i regret just not doing anything to protect myself. i didn't fight back. he was stronger than me, for one thing. i just let him do it....i was scared. i just went about my day like normal. it was killing me on the inside. i'm 19, almost 20, and it still doesn't get any easier 😢

there's other people out there who have gone through this as well. the past doesn't define who we are, we just got to move forward.☺️

text:
a woman who almost died through physical abuse
tricia st john is a tall chocolate woman with a kind smile and an overwhelming peace that permeates the room when she walks in. but also noticeable is the absence of her left forearm, two missing fingers from her right hand, multiple scars about her shoulders and cascading her neck, with a single three-inch long imprint lining her left temple—disfigurements sustained by chop wounds from the wielding cutlass of an angry ex.

on april 2, 2004, st john, of south trinidad, almost met her death as she lay in a crouched position on her neighbour’s front porch feeling each impact of the swinging blade.recounting the events of that horrifying evening, st john, who lived in port-of-spain at the time, had gone to her mother’s san fernando property to visit her three sons who were being kept from her by their father.

he was subsequently convicted of attempted murder with grievous bodily harm and was sentenced in 2009 to 25 years imprisonment with ten strokes.
“within those fives years that he remained free, he could have finished me off at anytime or attack another woman. for victims this is a hellish ordeal and they are made to feel demeaned, appearing before magistrate after magistrate, telling the story over and over for years before an actual trial takes place.” but st john had a message to send to the authorities—it is important that discrimination ends against people with disabilities.“"i obtained these physical challenges through abuse. i did not do it to myself. and it does not matter how someone obtains a physical impairment. what matters is that we are still human beings who are still alive and want to live and live the best life that we can". #domesticviolence #abuse #mentalhealth #narcissisticabuse #sociopath #narcissist #domesticviolenceawareness #gaslighting #metoo #emotionalabuse #domesticabuse #mentalhealthawareness #sexualabuse #love #toxicpeople #verbalabuse #trauma #psychologicalabuse #domesticviolencesurvivor #narc #ptsd #divorce #stoptheviolence #suicideprevention #endthestigma #survivor #stopthestigma #narcawareness #suicidal #bhfyp

text:
as long as there is no justice in the congo, there will not be justice anywhere else.

silicon valley would not exist without the congo, nor would anything else that is ‘digital’, including our way of life in the 4th industrial revolution.

i often think about powerful movements such as #blacklivesmatter & #metoo -  that are great examples of what is possible in the digital age - and if they have room to acknowledge that #hashtags contain congolese blood; blood from black women who are having their genitals mutilated - all in the name of an ongoing genocidal war fueled by the global demand for digital technology.

we are all complicit. 
the congo is the most important piece on the chessboard. 
when the fire of xangô hits the congo, it will lay the foundation for all on this earth to have justice.

text:
when maria gallagher and ana maria archila confronted then sen. jeff flake, it was dr. ford's testimony that inspired them.  maria explained in an interview with  harper's bazaar: "i knew friends who had been looked away from, and in the broader sense, that's how i felt dr. blasey ford was [treated]. everyone looked at her, listened to her, and turned away—they just completely looked away from all of her pain and suffering because they didn't want to confront it. that's literally what [flake] was doing right in front of me...." i wanted to commemorate this moment with a piece because it takes a lot of courage not only to tell your story but also to force others to engage with your story.  see strategy 4. .
.

text:
with india s biggest director accused by his own assistant for sexual assault , the  few blind articles , his name being taken off as the co-producer from sonam kapoor s upcoming release suddenly make sense. . .
yes this might seem like an inappropriate time to bring this up , but i really feel like penning down my views. this is about the movie which broke all records and was the first indian movie to rake in a whooping 200 crores. yes three idiots. its much loved by the audience and labelled as a family movie but i could not digest the way rape was turned into a joke. the lewd jokes on a woman's breasts and the balatkar /chamatkar jokes literallymade me cringe . rape is not an issue which can be made fun of , in whatever situation but i was shocked at the way this scene was casually swept under the rug. no hue and cry , absolutely no mention of this disgusting five minutes scene by the pseudointellectuals makes you believe that the bigger your name in bollywood you will escape scott free from the repercussions.

ok coming back to the present looks like the shit just hit the ceiling ! hope more women come out and no abuser walks away from their crimes. in this particular scenario i really hope and pray that in this battle david again wins against goliath ! more power to each victim who takes a stand for themselves and speak to finally , we are with you ❤❤❤
#empoweringwomen #metoo #metooindia #metoomovement #mompresso #bollywood #rookiemums #likeforlikes #instamoms #speakup #takeastand

text:
👉🏾👉🏾 as reported this past week, mystikal has his bond set at $3 million, and until the prospects of leaving his containment cell were looking grim. but as tmz is reporting, mystikal's attorney joel pearce is rounding up financial contributions from the rappers' friends and family. pearce is also counting on the proceeds from a recently-signed record deal which calls for mystikal to hand over three separate albums he'd already completed.

pearce fell short of a dollar amount estimate of where they currently sit in the donation. that said, pierce remains confident his client will be out on bail by the end of next week. for added context, mystikal was awarded a new judge in the case over his first-degree rape and second-degree kidnapping charges. this past week, joel pearce echoed his client's persistence with a pr message of sorts. "i don’t think that anyone should be made to stand trial for number one, something they did not do,” pearce told the media. text:
if you find yourself feeling like you can’t ever do anything right, it’s not you. narcissists will always change not only their expectations, they will confuse you. gaslighting. crazy making. for example, mine one time told me to say “yes” or “ok” when he was talking to me to make sure i was listening. the next time he was talking to me, i was saying “yes” and “ok” and he told me to stop being a smartass and to respond with appropriate answers that pertained to the conversation (mind you they will talk and talk and talk and ask seven different questions without taking a breath which ultimately confuses you so you’re not sure what to address and sometimes you forgot what you were even talking about to begin with!) so one of two things would happen: i would either try to respond as he was speaking to try and keep up and he would tell me to stop interrupting, or i would ask what he wanted me to address and i would be accused of not paying attention. kind of hard to hit a moving target which is what meeting expectations with a narcissist is 🤷🏻‍♀️

text:
this has got me in my feels!! @sharifafrc babe! this honestly has to be one of the most thought provoking posts. this was originally posted by @tiffanyjanay. 
reading this brought back to the last time i had sex. it was awful!! fucking awful.. the energy was off.. there was no consideration for me, it was selfish act of him getting his rocks off, if i hadn’t been there before with a previous ex i think i would of cried.. sex with this man wasn’t always like that, sometimes it was amazing but this one time was i believe for a couple of reasons - 1 because of his resentment towards me because i fell out of love with him 2 because the universe gave me bad dick so i wouldn’t crave it!! lol and could focus on my healing.. however the taste left in my mouth from it is 😶 he disrespected me in that moment but he wasn’t the first but for sure that last. @tiffanyjanay words resonate deep within my ancient dna 🧬 because i believe this to be true, the act of making love is precious, divine magic. -
-however now let’s role reverse this- if a man reflects the masculine aspect of herself wtf does that say about her? with so many of us women affected by #metoo and men letting us down left right and centre, no wonder our divine masculine is distorted. i have been healing on the balance of the divine masculine & feminine for nearly a year now and i can see small changes. there are good men & women out there, just make sure you are one of them. healing on self first before we jump into a relationship is imperative to not repeating the cycle. stop heal breath... you have time ❤️

text:
as a kid
i heard
that every time you say
you don't believe in magic
a fairy dies.

then i realized
how many non-believers there were.

as a woman, i learned
that every time you say
you don't believe a rape,
a victim dies.

then i realized,
how many non-believers there are.

this world has prioritized 
abusers lies,
sought to ensure
that magic dies.

but somehow, 
both women
and fairies 
survive.

we sustain our own magic. 
we believe in ourselves.
we stay alive. ~
#endviolenceagainstwomen 
#believevictims

text:
“create of our lives a masterpiece.” joseph b. wirthlin from his talk titled the abundant life.
.
i can’t stop looking at this collage my sister @the_librarycard made me, i love it! it goes along perfectly with that quote. it would be hard for anyone looking at this collage to know that at one point my husband i’m still married to had packed up his things and moved out, asking for a divorce. the church i belong to had scheduled a meeting in which they would decide if i could even still be a member of their organization. i was standing at a point in my life where i got to chose if i was going to fight. was i going to fight for my family? for the church i loved and wanted to be a part of? typing this actually makes me teary eyed. that part of my life was so dang hard! #asoulsurvivorspiritual
.
i did chose to fight. but make no mistake about it, it was a lot of hard work, time and sacrifice!
.
but here is the awesome thing you guys...
.
we can actually create a masterpiece of our lives.
.
we get to do that! we get to do it every! single! day! make our lives a masterpiece! through the choices we make, the thoughts we think, the things we do, we get to create whatever we want out of our lives! you guys, if you want something, you have to create it. you have to make it happen. the life we want doesn’t just come to us, wrapped in a present with a bow on top. we have to work to create it.
.
want to lose weight?
want to have a better marriage?
want to eat more veggies?
want to be more active? 
want to connect with your kids?
.
i have seen the difference in a life that i just let happen versus the one that i create and i am here to tell you that the one that takes work and sacrifice is hands down the one worth living.
.
i know, i know …  i’m like super late to the new year party but regardless, i am so pumped about the things i am creating for 2019! join me and let’s create of our lives a masterpiece!

text:
campaigners say attempts to reduce domestic violence are not working because the number of women killed by men has remained steady for the last decade.

at least 139 women were murdered by a man last year – including 21 killed in terrorist attacks – according to the latest femicide census report.
one report said a victim had been stabbed 175 times, while other women were described as having been “hit 40 times with an axe”, “bludgeoned repeatedly” and “battered virtually beyond all recognition”.
three quarters of the victims last year were killed by someone they knew. almost half of the perpetrators were partners or former partners of their victim.

nearly two thirds of the women were killed at home, while more than half of the cases involving a former intimate partner happened during the first month of separation. 
#domesticabuse #domesticviolence #stopabuse #youcanspeakup #reachout #womenarenotobjects #metoo #yourestrong #youreworthy #youreallyouneedtobe #gethelp #yourenotalone #justice

three quarters of the victims last year were killed by someone they knew. almost half of the perpetrators were partners or former partners of their victim.

nearly two thirds of the women were killed at home, while more than half of the cases involving a former intimate partner happened during the first month of separation.

text:
mystikal could be walking out of jail as early as next week if everything goes to plan. according to tmz, a combination of funds from friends and a new record deal could lead to his release from caddo correctional center before his trial for first degree rape and second-degree kidnapping starts this spring.
mystikal's attorney, joel pearce, told the celebrity news outlet that his client's friends and family have been raising money for his $3 million bond but it was a newly-signed record deal that really helped him reach his goal.

according to tim yazbeck, another lawyer for the embattled rhymer, his new deal consist of him recording three unreleased albums. he's hoping to get an advance within days. mystikal's legal team is confident that the rapper can post bail and be released by the end of next week.

the ghetto fabulous artist has been behind bars since august 2017 after an unnamed woman accused both him and another man, averweone darnell holman, of raping her in may 2017. the alleged rape took place in october 2016. holman faces the same charges. a third person, a woman named tenichia monieck wafford, has also been charged with obstruction of justice in relation to the alleged assault for reportedly trying to persuade the woman to recant her story.
mystikal, whose real name is michael tyler, has denied all rape allegations against him and believes the entire situation was fueled by the #metoo movement that has exposed sexual misconduct by male executives and celebrities in the film and music industry.
mystikal’s rape trial is expected to start in may.
.
.
.
.

text:
over the past year, i’ve been trying, trying, being the key word to eat healthier. i’m trying to change my poor eating habits into good ones! i partnered with @threefarmersfoods and tried out all 4 flavours of their new crunchy little lentils (lightly salted, sea salt and vinegar, barbeque, and garlic and herb). i had tried their chickpeas and roasted peapops on my own over the holidays. 
its hard to retrain old habits when snacking, but it’s so much easier when the snack tastes good and actually satisfies me! i would grab a bag of these and do my netflix, e-mail shuffle all month! #partner #threefarmers #threefarmersfoods #healthysnacks

text:
this article from ucla lecturer and author kim elsesser shows that despite all the progress that's been made in recent years, we're still extremely distant from most men caring about equality - and when men care about their female workmates, it's mostly because they're afraid their sexual misdemeanours will be outed.
this misogynist attitude has to undergo radical change! in the place of the patriarchal system where women rely on men caring about their issues, we have to usher in an era where women have full and true control of their own lives and bodies, and will never be secondary to men in their occupations!

the full article - https://www.forbes.com/sites/kimelsesser/2019/01/10/of-all-the-gender-issues-at-work-men-are-most-concerned-about-false-harassment-claims-from-women/

text:
french montana speaks on the allegations against r. kelly.

the most talked about topic this past week has been the allegations against r. kelly. after lifetime aired their docuseries surviving r. kelly which explores the numerous allegations of sexual misconduct by the singer over the years. everyone’s been sharing their opinions on the matter including french montana who seems to believe that despite the horrific accusations r. kelly faces, the chicago singer should be able to enjoy his musical legacy.

tmz recently caught up with french montana who shared a contentious opinion on r. kelly. while many are hoping to see r. kelly behind bars, french believes that kellz should be able to enjoy his legacy as an artist regardless of whether he’s a sexual predator or not. the rapper even name-dropped michael jackson while he was at it. “all the greats went down like that,” he said.

adding, “let somebody enjoy their legacy. whatever happened, happened, man.” french did, however, mention that these allegations shouldn’t be shocking to anyone. r. kelly did mention it in his songs. french referenced the “bump n grind” line, “my mind’s tellin’ me no, but my body, my body’s tellin’ me yes” to make his point.

when asked if people should stop listening to his music, french simply replied, “they [people] don’t let nobody have their legendary moments.” peep the clip in the full story at www.itskenbarbie.com (or swipe) what do you guys think? #french #montana #frenchmontana #rkelly #muterkelly #robertkelly #survivingrkelly #metoo #trappedinthecloset #entertainment #entertainmentnews #entertainmentblog #gossip

text:
someone asked me the other day about the #blackgirlmagic✨ movement, and i wasn't entirely satisfied with my response at the time. so, i thought i would give myself a second chance. see, i need #blackwomen and #blackgirls and the #blackgirlmagic✨💫 movement not only because society renders us invisible but by default those whom are invisible are also unprotected. and those whom are unprotected are easily excusable. there is no justice for raping a ghost, and there is no justice for killing ghosts either.i need #blackgirlmagic because of #niawilson, #rekiaboyd, #cyntoiabrown and #jazminebarnes and every unnamed black girl and woman that hasn't survived or named. i need it because #bringbackdcgirls and#mmiw. i need #blackgirlmagic because #survivingrkelly and #anitahill. i need #blackgirlmagic because #ayanapressley and #michelleobama are only the beginning. i need #blackgirlmagic because even #serenawilliams has to save her own life. i need #blackgirlmagic because #medicalracism and #educationalracism. i need #blackgirlmagic because it is 2019 and i am a first generation college graduate. because black women rank near the lowest paid per hour. i need #blackgirlmagic because when a brown boy sexually assaulted me no one cared until he assaulted a white girl. i need #blackgirlmagic because black girls are sexualized as an excuse for rape. when a 16 year old white boy sexually assaulted me i "wanted it." i was 8 years old. i need #blackgirlmagic because until the safety and protection of black women and girls becomes a priority, we will sacrifice the most. our dignity. our mental health. i need blackgirlmagic because merely surviving isn't living. we rise on the shoulders of our ancestors but we also rise with our sisters and mothers and daughters. #phenomenalwomen
#metoo #yesalldaughters #blacklivesmatter #blackwomen #believesurvivors #muterkelly #browngirl

text:
#metoo #timesup #muterkelly  #godsaystimesup  my next book, "the me too movement of the bible." understanding the will of god through the word of god and the me too movement

i had great hesitation in writing a book about the me too movement and the bible. in my hesitation, i begin to think that maybe a woman should write this book. in this book, i would be challenged to write about things that most preachers never preach or teach in their bible lessons. the sunday school lessons that are written never deal with the issue of sexual assault. most books that are written in the christian arena never deal with the issues that will be discussed in this book. i am about to write about something that if i came across in a movie, i would turn the movie off because i do not find such matters entertaining even in the world of make-believe movies.

but in dealing with these kinds of issues in real life you can't turn it off. you can't fast forward through the scenes that you don't like in real life. many who will read this book wish they could turn it off or fast forward through the pain. this book is a book written for all the silent victims of sexual harassment and sexual assault.  i pray that god will use this book to heal all the hurt and the shame that surrounds these heinous crimes.

coming spring 2019 ...take a look at dr. eaton's other books at 
amazon.com/author/revdrmichaeleaton

text:
my wings have been clipped for most of my life. however, today i'm no longer afraid of soaring!

growing up, fear was instilled in me non-stop.

about everything.

about being an illegal immigrant.
about not behaving or else.
about my mother’s schizophrenia and how it was supposedly my fault.
so i was afraid i caused her maniac episodes.
about how as a teenager, i could get pregnant.
that was my welcome message to my first period.
i didn’t understand what that really meant.
i was afraid of being a woman.
of being poor.
of being sent back to mexico by my family as punishment.
by immigration.
of driving.
of going to college.
of having a job.
i was the most naive teenager.

i literally cried myself to sleep as a young child because i was afraid of so many things.
my little self couldn’t handle the pressure of the burden of fear i was given.
so i cried. all.the.time.
the kind of crying that hurts the soul.
the crying that with every tear drop i felt a deep pain in my lungs.
my crying was the silent kind.
i wasn’t able to show it because i would get in trouble.
so i cried myself to sleep every night.

those many fears continued into my young adult life.
i was afraid of not succeeding.
then i became afraid of succeeding.
i was afraid i was not good enough.
i was afraid of being myself because i was never accepted to be me.
i was too bossy.
too outspoken.
too demanding.
too assertive.
afraid to let the fat go that had protected me from being too beautiful.
too attractive.
too powerful.
from being raped again.

no surprise, i married someone who kept the pattern going.
clipping my wings using religion and submission.
saying no to almost everything i wanted.
i did it anyway but the pain of not being supported hurt me deeply.
i was afraid to disappoint god and so i stayed much longer than i needed.

until i faced my fears, one by one. 
cont'd in comments but also published on @itwasneveradress.  link in bio
.
.
.
.
#empoweredwomen #empoweringwomen #mystory #metoo #itwasneveradress #mujeres #empoderamento #healingenergy #healingmyself #goodbyefear #innerchildhealing #newyear #2019life

text: there have been several moments of trauma in my life where i look back and feel guilty for how i responded. i feel the weight of shame that comes along with not overpowering my assailant, for not reporting it or for not pressing charges. a recent occurrence included a stranger who pinned me in a booth while he was assaulting me - me, a physically strong, loud, doesn’t-put-up-with-crap woman. i was still wearing my church t-shirt and my church name-tag around my neck. a woman i taught with was on the other side of the restaurant with her husband who is a very well-known principal. i shut down, i didn’t push him and i didn’t scream. i froze. i hoped that the waitress could tell i was in distress, or the girl i taught with would know this man wasn't my husband and say something. i did my best to make it clear i was not interested and that he needed to leave me alone. when i look back at that situation, i often get angry that i didn’t push him, scream at him and make a scene. i had nothing to be embarrassed about because i was doing nothing wrong, but yet i felt the pressure to not draw attention to myself. maybe someone would recognize my church name and find out the screaming lady at the restaurant actually worked for that church. i was afraid to cause a scene in front of a friend and her husband, the principal. i was afraid to cause disruption that would make all eyes turn on me. but a friend of mine reminded me that i am safe now and that in those moments i relied on survival patterns and traits that i picked up on while i’ve endured trauma in the past. she didn’t tell me to forgive myself for not knowing better, or forgive myself for giving away my power, or forgive myself for those survival patterns, but instead told me to thank my body for doing what i needed to get home safe. if you didn’t respond to trauma the way you thought you would remember that you’re not the one who should feel shame - you didn’t do anything wrong - the trauma you faced is not a reflection of who you are. if you’re recovering from trauma, i highly recommend seeking help from a trauma therapist. hear me say - you are not at fault and your trauma will not define you.
name: Courtney Holden

me, a physically strong, loud, doesn’t-put-up-with-crap woman. i was still wearing my church t-shirt and my church name-tag around my neck. a woman i taught with was on the other side of the restaurant with her husband who is a very well-known principal. i shut down, i didn’t push him and i didn’t scream. i froze. i hoped that the waitress could tell i was in distress, or the girl i taught with would know this man wasn't my husband and say something. i did my best to make it clear i was not interested and that he needed to leave me alone. when i look back at that situation, i often get angry that i didn’t push him, scream at him and make a scene. i had nothing to be embarrassed about because i was doing nothing wrong, but yet i felt the pressure to not draw attention to myself. maybe someone would recognize my church name and find out the screaming lady at the restaurant actually worked for that church. i was afraid to cause a scene in front of a friend and her husband, the principal. i was afraid to cause disruption that would make all eyes turn on me. but a friend of mine reminded me that i am safe now and that in those moments i relied on survival patterns and traits that i picked up on while i’ve endured trauma in the past. she didn’t tell me to forgive myself for not knowing better, or forgive myself for giving away my power, or forgive myself for those survival patterns, but instead told me to thank my body for doing what i needed to get home safe. if you didn’t respond to trauma the way you thought you would remember that you’re not the one who should feel shame - you didn’t do anything wrong - the trauma you faced is not a reflection of who you are. if you’re recovering from trauma, i highly recommend seeking help from a trauma therapist. hear me say - you are not at fault and your trauma will not define you.

text:
calling all indigenous women of the americas!  native american/indigenous women are invited to join kanyon sayers-roods, aurora mamea, marge grow eppard & annita luchessi at the san francisco women's march.  kanyon sayers-roods will open the rally with a traditional ohlone welcome.  aurora mamea, annita luchessi & marge grow will share the stage to speak out for our missing & murdered indigenous women. (please share and tag yourself). meet at 10am on the right side of the stage to gather in prayer. 
women will be invited to stand in front of the stage as our sisters are speaking on the stage.

we will lead the march together behind a #mmiw banner after the rally at the civic center.

wear red. make a sign - some suggestions:

trauma to indigenous women = trauma to mother earth #mmiw

untold numbers of missing & murdered indigenous women #mmiw

we stand together #mmiw

not only #metoo also #mmiw

see you there ladies!

text:
calling all indigenous women of the americas!  native american/indigenous women are invited to join kanyon sayers-roods, aurora mamea, marge grow eppard & annita luchessi at the san francisco women's march.  kanyon sayers-roods will open the rally with a traditional ohlone welcome.  aurora mamea, annita luchessi & marge grow will share the stage to speak out for our missing & murdered indigenous women. (please share and tag yourself). meet at 10am on the right side of the stage to gather in prayer. 
women will be invited to stand in front of the stage as our sisters are speaking on the stage.

we will lead the march together behind a #mmiw banner after the rally at the civic center.

wear red. make a sign - some suggestions:

trauma to indigenous women = trauma to mother earth #mmiw

untold numbers of missing & murdered indigenous women #mmiw

we stand together #mmiw

not only #metoo also #mmiw

see you there ladies!

text:
30 democrats in puerto rico with 109 lobbyists for the weekend despite shutdown:
⠀⠀⠀
some 30 democratic lawmakers left the government shutdown behind friday on a chartered flight to puerto rico for a winter retreat with 109 lobbyists and corporate executives during which they planned to see the hit broadway show “hamilton” and attend three parties including one with the show’s cast.
⠀⠀⠀
those attending the congressional hispanic caucus bold pac winter retreat in san juan planned to meet with key officials to discuss the cleanup after hurricane maria at a roundtable saturday.
⠀⠀⠀
but the weekend is packed with free time for the members and their families on the trip.
⠀⠀⠀
some 109 lobbyists and corporate executives are named in the memo, a rate of 3.6 lobbyists for every member. they include those from several big k street firms, r.j. reynolds, facebook, comcast, amazon, phrma, microsoft, intel, verizon, and unions like the national education association.

text: as for many, many people, the #metoo movement made me reflect on things that happened to myself and my friends that were simply not ok. i made these two paintings last year and they are in my current exhibition “blessings” @roslynoxley9 with “sexual healing” i was trying to find to way to illustrate a journey from trauma to healing. that it’s like the extra leaf on the clover we are looking for - that healing is possible. and that since ‘me too’ hopefully many people feel less shame talking about and sharing their experiences, both from the past and as they happen in the present, leading to cycle of healing. with “especially for you” i say what i mean. #sexualhealing #especiallyforyou #sayingwhatimean #blessings #painting #roslynoxley9 #nellartist
